<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse &uuml;lesanne </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of Act </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolev seadus s&auml;testab riikliku pensioni m&otilde;iste, liigid, riikliku pensionikindlustuse korralduse, riikliku pensionikindlustuse vahendite arvestamise alused, samuti riikliku pensionikindlustuse registri loomise ja pidamise alused ning riikliku pensioni m&auml;&auml;ramise, arvutamise ja maksmise tingimused ning korra. </eesti>
<inglise>This Act provides the definition and classes of state pension, the organisation of state pension insurance, the bases for calculation of funds for state pension insurance, the bases for establishment and maintenance of the state pension insurance register, and the conditions and procedure for the grant, calculation and payment of state pensions. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of state pension </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel makstav riiklik pension on solidaarsusp&otilde;him&otilde;ttele tuginev igakuine rahaline sotsiaalkindlustush&uuml;vitis vanaduse, t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse v&otilde;i toitja kaotuse korral, mida makstakse riigieelarves riikliku pensionikindlustuse kuludeks m&auml;&auml;ratud vahenditest. </eesti>
<inglise>A state pension payable on the basis of this Act is a monthly financial social insurance benefit in the case of old age, incapacity for work or loss of a provider which is based on the principle of solidarity and which is paid from the funds allocated for the expenditure of state pension insurance in the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensionikindlustatu </eesti>
<inglise>Assured persons </inglise>
<eesti>Pensionikindlustatu on isik: </eesti>
<inglise>Assured persons are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kes vastavalt sotsiaalmaksuseadusele (RT I 1998, 40, 611; 61, 982; 113/114, 1876; 1999, 29, 379; 71, 685; 82, 749; 88, 806; 97, 857; 101, 903) on maksnud v&otilde;i kelle eest on kohustus maksta sotsiaalmaksu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) persons who pursuant to the Social Tax Act (RT I 1998, 40, 611; 61, 982; 113/114, 1876; 1999, 29, 379; 71, 685; 82, 749; 88, 806; 97, 857; 101, 903) pay social tax or for whom social tax shall be paid; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kellel vastavalt k&auml;esolevale seadusele tekib muudel alustel &otilde;igus riiklikule pensionile. </eesti>
<inglise>2) persons for whom the right to receive a state pension arises on other bases pursuant to this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni saamise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to receive state pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklik pension m&auml;&auml;ratakse ja makstakse Eesti alalisele elanikule v&otilde;i t&auml;htajalise elamisloa alusel Eestis elavale v&auml;lismaalasele pensioni saamise &otilde;iguse tekkimisel k&auml;esoleva seadusega etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) State pensions shall be granted and paid to permanent residents of Estonia and aliens residing in Estonia on the basis of temporary residence permits if the right to receive a pension arises in the cases prescribed by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eestis viibival pagulasel on riikliku pensioni saamise &otilde;igus Eesti alalise elanikuga v&otilde;rdsetel alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Refugees staying in Estonia have the right to receive state pensions on equal bases with permanent residents of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel m&auml;&auml;ratakse riiklik pension juhul, kui isik ei saa riiklikku pensioni Eesti teiste seaduste alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A state pension shall be granted pursuant to this Act unless a person receives a state pension pursuant to other Estonian Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui Eesti Vabariigi poolt s&otilde;lmitud v&auml;lisleping sisaldab pensioni m&auml;&auml;ramiseks ja maksmiseks teistsuguseid s&auml;tteid kui k&auml;esolev seadus, siis kohaldatakse v&auml;lislepingut. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an international agreement entered into by the Republic of Estonia contains provisions which differ from this Act for the grant and payment of pensions, the international agreement applies. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni liigid </eesti>
<inglise>Classes of state pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev seadus s&auml;testab j&auml;rgmised riikliku pensioni liigid: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act provides for the following state pensions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vanaduspension; </eesti>
<inglise>1) old-age pension; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension; </eesti>
<inglise>2) pension for incapacity for work; </inglise>
<eesti>3) toitjakaotuspension; </eesti>
<inglise>3) survivor's pension; </inglise>
<eesti>4) rahvapension. </eesti>
<inglise>4) national pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikule, kellel on &otilde;igus mitmele k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis loetletud riikliku pensioni liigile, m&auml;&auml;ratakse &uuml;ks liik tema valikul, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Persons who have the right to receive several classes of state pension listed in this section shall be granted one class of their choice, with the exception of persons specified in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Alla 18-aastasel v&otilde;i alla 24-aastasel orvul, kes &otilde;pib g&uuml;mnaasiumi v&otilde;i kutse&otilde;ppeasutuse p&auml;evases &otilde;ppevormis v&otilde;i &uuml;likooli v&otilde;i rakendusk&otilde;rgkooli statsionaarses &otilde;ppevormis, v&otilde;i sellest east vanemal orvul, kui ta on tunnistatud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks enne 18-aastaseks (p&auml;evases v&otilde;i statsionaarses &otilde;ppevormis &otilde;ppija enne 24-aastaseks) saamist, on &otilde;igus saada, arvestades k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 14 l&otilde;ike 2 ja &sect; 16 l&otilde;ike 2 punkti 3 s&auml;tteid, samaaegselt kahte toitjakaotuspensioni v&otilde;i kahte rahvapensioni v&otilde;i nii toitjakaotuspensioni kui rahvapensioni s&otilde;ltuvalt tema vanemate pensioni&otilde;iguslikust v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;ist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Persons who are under 18 years of age, or orphans who are under 24 years of age, and who are enrolled in daytime study at an upper secondary school or vocational educational institution or in full-time study at a university or institution of applied higher education, or orphans who are older if they were declared incapacitated for work before they attained 18 years of age (or if they are students enrolled in daytime or full-time study, before they attained 24 years of age) have the right, taking into account the provisions of subsection 14 (2) and clause 16 (2) 3) of this Act, to receive two survivor's pensions or two national pensions or both a survivor's pension and a national pension concurrently, depending on the years of pensionable service or the accumulation period of their parents. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857; 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857; 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensionikindlustuse korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of state pension insurance </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklikku pensionikindlustust korraldab Sotsiaalministeeriumi valitsemisalas olev Sotsiaalkindlustusamet elukohaj&auml;rgsete pensioniametite kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>State pension insurance shall be organised by the Social Insurance Board in the area of government of the Ministry of Social Affairs through local pension offices. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Vanaduspension </eesti>
<inglise>Old-Age Pension </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus vanaduspensionile </eesti>
<inglise>Right to receive old-age pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;igus vanaduspensionile on 63-aastaseks saanud v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 m&auml;rgitud vanuses oleval isikul, kellel on v&auml;hemalt 15 aastat Eestis omandatud pensioni&otilde;iguslikku staa&zcaron;i v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Persons who have attained 63 years of age or who are of an age set out in subsection (2) of this section and who have completed at least fifteen years of pensionable service or whose accumulation period acquired in Estonia is at least fifteen years have the right to receive an old-age pension. </inglise>
<eesti>Enne k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud ea saabumist tekib meestel ja naistel &otilde;igus vanaduspensionile allj&auml;rgnevalt s&auml;testatud vanuses: </eesti>
<inglise>Before attaining the age provided for in subsection (1) of this section, the right of men and women to receive an old-age pension arises at the ages provided as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Ennet&auml;htaegne vanaduspension </eesti>
<inglise>Early-retirement pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ennet&auml;htaegse vanaduspensioni saamise &otilde;igus tekib mitte varem kui kolm aastat enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud vanusesse j&otilde;udmist isikul, kellel on vanaduspensioni m&auml;&auml;ramiseks n&otilde;utav &sect; 7 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud pensioni&otilde;iguslik v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The right of a person to receive an early-retirement pension arises not earlier than three years before the person attains the age provided for in subsection 7 (1) of this Act and if the years of pensionable service or the accumulation period provided for in subsection 7 (1) of this Act of the person are sufficient for the grant of an old-age pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikul, kellel tema s&uuml;nniaasta kohaselt tekib &otilde;igus vanaduspensionile vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;ikele 2, on ennet&auml;htaegse vanaduspensioni saamise &otilde;igus mitte varem kui kolm aastat enne &sect; 7 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud vanadusse j&otilde;udmist, kui tal on vanaduspensioni m&auml;&auml;ramiseks n&otilde;utav &sect; 7 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud pensioni&otilde;iguslik v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person whose right to receive an old-age pension arises pursuant to subsection 7 (2) of this Act according to his or her year of birth has the right to receive an early-retirement pension not earlier than three years before attaining the age provided for in subsection 7 (2) and if the years of pensionable service or the accumulation period provided for in subsection 7 (1) of the person are sufficient for the grant of an old-age pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ennet&auml;htaegne vanaduspension arvutatakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses vanaduspensioni arvutamiseks ja &uuml;mberarvutamiseks kehtestatud korras, v&auml;hendades pensioni iga k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 etten&auml;htud pensionieast varem pensionile j&auml;&auml;mise kuu eest 0,4 protsendi v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An early-retirement pension shall be calculated pursuant to the procedure for calculation and recalculation of old-age pensions established by this Act, which reduces the pension by 0.4 per cent for every month of retirement prior to the pensionable age prescribed in subsections 7 (1) or (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ennet&auml;htaegne vanaduspension m&auml;&auml;ratakse eluajaks ja seda ei arvutata &uuml;mber soodustingimustel vanaduspensioniks v&otilde;i vanaduspensioniks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Early-retirement pensions are granted for life and shall not be recalculated as old-age pensions under favourable conditions or old-age pensions. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus soodustingimustel vanaduspensionile </eesti>
<inglise>Right to receive old-age pension under favourable conditions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;igus soodustingimustel vanaduspensionile tekib: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The right to receive an old-age pension under favourable conditions arises: </inglise>
<eesti>1) emal, isal, v&otilde;&otilde;rasvanemal, eestkostjal v&otilde;i hooldajal - viis aastat enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud vanusesse j&otilde;udmist, kui tal on v&auml;hemalt 15 aastat pensioni&otilde;iguslikku v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i ja kui ta on kasvatanud v&auml;hemalt kaheksa aastat lapsinvaliidi, alla 18-aastast keskmise, raske v&otilde;i s&uuml;gava puudega last, alla 18-aastast invaliidi lapseeast v&otilde;i viit v&otilde;i enamat last; </eesti>
<inglise>1) five years before attaining the age prescribed in subsections 7 (1) or (2) of this Act for a mother, father, step-parent, guardian or caregiver who, for at least eight years, has raised a disabled child, a child under 18 years of age with a moderate, severe or profound disability, a child under 18 years of age who is disabled from childhood, or five or more children, if he or she has completed at least fifteen years of pensionable service or his or her accumulation period is at least fifteen years; </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146; 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146; 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>2) emal v&otilde;i isal v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;rasvanemal v&otilde;i eestkostjal v&otilde;i hooldajal, kes on kasvatanud v&auml;hemalt kaheksa aastat nelja last, - kolm aastat v&otilde;i kolme last - &uuml;ks aasta enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 etten&auml;htud vanusesse j&otilde;udmist, kui tal on v&auml;hemalt 15 aastat pensioni&otilde;iguslikku v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i; </eesti>
<inglise>2) three years before attaining the age prescribed in subsections 7 (1) or (2) of this Act for a mother, father, step-parent, guardian or caregiver who has raised four children for at least eight years, or one year before attaining the age prescribed in subsections 7 (1) or (2) of this Act for a mother, father, guardian or caregiver who has raised three children for at least eight years, if he or she has completed at least fifteen years of pensionable service or his or her accumulation period is at least fifteen years; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>3) h&uuml;pof&uuml;saarse k&auml;&auml;buskasvuga isikul - 45-aastaseks saanud naisel v&otilde;i mehel, kellel on v&auml;hemalt 15 aastat pensioni&otilde;iguslikku v&otilde;i pensioni-kindlustusstaa&zcaron;i; </eesti>
<inglise>3) persons suffering from pituitary dwarfism - persons who have attained 45 years of age and who have completed at least fifteen years of pensionable service or whose accumulation period is at least fifteen years; </inglise>
<eesti>4) isikul, kes v&otilde;ttis osa T&scaron;ernob&otilde;li aatomielektrijaama avarii tagaj&auml;rgede likvideerimisest, viis aastat enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 etten&auml;htud vanusesse j&otilde;udmist, kui tal on v&auml;hemalt 15 aastat pensioni&otilde;iguslikku v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i; </eesti>
<inglise>4) persons who participated in the clean-up of the accident at the Chernobyl nuclear power station, five years before attaining the age prescribed in subsections 7 (1) or (2) of this Act, if they have completed at least fifteen years of pensionable service or their accumulation period is at least fifteen years; </inglise>
<eesti>5) rehabiliteeritud isikul, kes &otilde;igusvastaselt represseerituna on viibinud kinnipidamiskohas v&otilde;i asumisel. </eesti>
<inglise>5) rehabilitated persons who have been unlawfully held in a custodial institution or in exile. </inglise>
<eesti>Temal v&auml;hendatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i 2 etten&auml;htud pensionile &otilde;igust andvat vanust &uuml;he aasta v&otilde;rra iga kinnipidamiskohas v&otilde;i asumisel viibitud t&auml;isaasta eest, ent kokku mitte rohkem kui viie aasta v&otilde;rra, kui tal on v&auml;hemalt 15 aastat pensioni&otilde;iguslikku v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i. </eesti>
<inglise>The pensionable age prescribed in subsections 7 (1) or (2) of this Act shall be reduced by one year for each full year they have been held in a custodial institution or in exile, but by not more than five years in total, if they have completed at least fifteen years of pensionable service or their accumulation period is at least fifteen years. </inglise>
<eesti>04.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 33, 194 </eesti>
<inglise>(04.04.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 33, 194) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 n&otilde;utud v&auml;hemalt 15-aastane pensioni&otilde;iguslik v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron; peab olema omandatud Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The fifteen years of pensionable service or the accumulation period of at least fifteen years required in subsection (1) of this section must be acquired in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Soodustingimustel vanaduspension m&auml;&auml;ratakse eluajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Old-age pensions under favourable conditions are granted for life. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension </eesti>
<inglise>Pension for Incapacity for Work </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensionile </eesti>
<inglise>Right to receive pension for incapacity for work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensionile on v&auml;hemalt 16-aastasel isikul kuni k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioniikka j&otilde;udmiseni, juhul kui ta on Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud korras tunnistatud p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotusega 40-100 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person has the right to receive a pension for incapacity for work from the age of 16 years until attaining the pensionable age provided for in subsections 7 (1) or (2) of this Act if he or she is declared permanently incapacitated for work with the 40 to 100 per cent loss of the capacity for work pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>P&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse korral, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 4 ja 4 (1) s&auml;testatud juhtudel, on &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensionile isikul, kellel pensioni m&auml;&auml;ramise algt&auml;htajaks on Eestis omandatud j&auml;rgmine pensioni&otilde;iguslik v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;: </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of permanent incapacity for work and except for the cases provided for in subsections (4) and (4 (1)) of this section, a person has the right to receive a pension for incapacity for work if he or she has completed the following years of pensionable service or acquired the following accumulation period in Estonia by the time the pension may be granted: </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857; 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857; 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui isik, kellele on m&auml;&auml;ratud ja makstud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni ning kelle &otilde;igus pensionile l&otilde;ppes p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse aja l&otilde;ppemise t&otilde;ttu, tunnistatakse korduvalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks, suurendatakse t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensionile &otilde;iguse kindlakstegemisel t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni eelmisel m&auml;&auml;ramisel kohaldatud pensioni&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i n&otilde;uet &uuml;he aasta v&otilde;rra iga kolme aasta kohta, mis on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud eelmise p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse l&otilde;ppemise ajast, kuid mitte enam kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud pensioni&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i n&otilde;udeni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a person to whom a pension for incapacity for work has been granted and paid and whose right to receive the pension has extinguished due to expiration of the period of permanent incapacity for work is repeatedly declared to be incapacitated for work, the requirement for years of pensionable service or the accumulation period applied upon the previous granting of a pension for incapacity for work shall be increased upon determination of the right to receive a pension for incapacity for work by one year for each three years which have passed from the expiration of the previous period of permanent incapacity for work, but not more than up to the requirement for years of pensionable service or the accumulation period provided for in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;vigastuse v&otilde;i kutsehaiguse tagaj&auml;rjel tekkinud p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse puhul on &otilde;igus saada t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni pensioni&otilde;iguslikust v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;ist olenemata. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the case of permanent incapacity for work arising from a work injury or occupational disease, a person has the right to receive a pension for incapacity for work regardless of his or her years of pensionable service or accumulation period. </inglise>
<eesti>(4 (1)) Kaitsev&auml;eteenistuses teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel v&otilde;i seoses teenistuskohustustega tekkinud p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse puhul on &otilde;igus saada t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni pensioni&otilde;iguslikust v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;ist olenemata. </eesti>
<inglise>(4 (1)) In the case of permanent incapacity for work arising from the performance of duties in the service of the armed forces, a person has the right to receive a pension for incapacity for work regardless of his or her years of pensionable service or accumulation period. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) P&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isikule m&auml;&auml;ratakse t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension kogu t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ajaks, kuid mitte kauemaks kui k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioniikka j&otilde;udmiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A person who is declared permanently incapacitated for work shall be granted a pension for incapacity for work for the whole period of incapacity for work, but for not longer than until he or she attains the pensionable age provided for in subsections 7 (1) or (2) of this Act. </inglise>
