<eesti>P&uuml;siv t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus </eesti>
<inglise>Permanent incapacity for work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) (Kehtetu - 08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(1) (Repealed - 08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&uuml;sival t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetusel on kaks astet - t&auml;ielik t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus ja osaline t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) There are two degrees of permanent incapacity for work - total incapacity for work and partial incapacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&auml;ielikult t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu on isik, kellel esineb haigusest v&otilde;i vigastusest p&otilde;hjustatud tugevasti v&auml;ljendunud funktsioonih&auml;ire, mille t&otilde;ttu ta ei ole v&otilde;imeline t&ouml;&ouml;ga elatist teenima. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person with a serious functional impairment caused by an illness or injury due to which he or she is not able to work in order to support himself or herself, is totally incapacitated for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Osaliselt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu on isik, kes on v&otilde;imeline t&ouml;&ouml;ga elatist teenima, kuid kes haigusest v&otilde;i vigastusest p&otilde;hjustatud funktsioonih&auml;ire t&otilde;ttu ei ole v&otilde;imeline tegema talle sobivat t&ouml;&ouml;d t&ouml;&ouml;aja &uuml;ldisele riiklikule normile vastavas mahus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person who is able to work in order to support himself or herself but who due to a functional impairment caused by an illness or injury is not able to perform work suitable for him or her in the amount corresponding to the general national standard for working time is partially incapacitated for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(4 (1)) P&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ulatust v&auml;ljendatakse t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotuse protsentides nulliga l&otilde;ppeva arvuna. </eesti>
<inglise>(4 (1)) The extent of permanent incapacity for work is expressed as a percentage of loss of capacity for work, by a number ending with zero. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(4 (2)) T&auml;ielikule t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetusele vastab t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotus 100 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4 (2)) A loss of 100 per cent of the capacity for work corresponds to total incapacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(4 (3)) Osalisele t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetusele vastab t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotus 10-90 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4 (3)) A loss of 10-90 per cent of the capacity for work corresponds to partial incapacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(4 (4)) Isiku v&otilde;ib p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks tunnistada kestusega kuus kuud, &uuml;ks aasta, kaks aastat, viis aastat v&otilde;i kuni k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioniikka j&otilde;udmiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4 (4)) A person may be declared permanently incapacitated for work for a period of six months, one year, two years, five years or until attaining a pensionable age provided for in subsections 7 (1) or (2) of this Act, </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(4 (5)) Isiku p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse tekkimise aja v&otilde;ib tuvastada tagasiulatuvalt, ent mitte enam kui kolm aastat arstliku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ekspertiisi taotlemise kuup&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(4 (5)) The time at which a person's permanent incapacity for work arises may be established retroactively but not later than three years after the date of application for a medical examination for incapacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) P&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse tekkimise aeg, p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse p&otilde;hjus ja p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse kestus tuvastatakse arstliku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ekspertiisiga Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The time at which permanent incapacity for work arises and the reason for and duration of permanent incapacity for work shall be established by a medical examination for incapacity for work pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotuse protsendi m&auml;&auml;ramise juhendi kinnitab ning arstlikku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ekspertiisi suunamiseks vajalikud dokumendid kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The guidelines for determination of the percentage of loss of capacity for work shall be approved and the documents necessary to be sent for a medical examination for incapacity for work shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857; 15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857; 15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Arstliku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ekspertiisi otsuse vormi kinnitab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The Minister of Social Affairs shall approve the form of the results of medical examinations for incapacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni arvutamise ja maksmise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications of calculation and payment of pension for incapacity for work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni arvutamise aluseks v&otilde;etakse suurem j&auml;rgnevatest: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The greatest of the following shall be the basis for calculation of a pension for incapacity for work: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu isiku pensioni&otilde;igusliku ja pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i alusel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 21 ja 22 s&auml;tete kohaselt arvutatud pension; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the pension of the person who is permanently incapacitated for work calculated on the basis of years of pensionable service and accumulation period pursuant to the provisions of &sect;&sect; 21 and 22 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vanaduspension 30-aastase pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i korral. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the old-age pension if the person has completed thirty years of pensionable service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension moodustab t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotusele vastava protsendi k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 alusel leitud suurusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The pension for incapacity for work is a percentage corresponding to the loss of capacity for work, of the amount calculated pursuant to subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 alusel arvutatud pension osutub v&auml;iksemaks rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast, makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a pension calculated pursuant to subsection (2) of this section is less than the national pension rate, the pension for incapacity for work shall be paid at the national pension rate. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Toitjakaotuspension </eesti>
<inglise>Survivor's Pension </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus toitjakaotuspensionile </eesti>
<inglise>Right to receive survivor's pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Toitjakaotuspension m&auml;&auml;ratakse toitja surma korral tema &uuml;lalpidamisel olnud perekonnaliikmele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the death of a provider, a survivor's pension shall be granted to family members who were maintained by him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>Lapsele, vanemale v&otilde;i lesele m&auml;&auml;ratakse pension s&otilde;ltumata sellest, kas nad olid toitja &uuml;lalpidamisel v&otilde;i mitte. </eesti>
<inglise>Children, parents and the widow or widower of the provider shall be granted a pension regardless of whether they were maintained by the provider or not. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eestis t&auml;htajalise elamisloaga elavale v&auml;lismaalasele m&auml;&auml;ratakse toitjakaotuspension t&auml;htajalise elamisloa kehtivuse perioodil, kui &otilde;igus sellele pensionile tekkis Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An alien residing in Estonia on the basis of a temporary residence permit shall be granted a survivor's pension during the term of the temporary residence permit if the right to receive the pension arises in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Toitjakaotuspensionile &otilde;igust omavaks perekonnaliikmeks on: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Family members who have the right to receive a survivor's pension are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) laps, vend, &otilde;de v&otilde;i lapselaps, kes on alla 18-aastane (alla 24-aastane g&uuml;mnaasiumi v&otilde;i kutse&otilde;ppeasutuse p&auml;evases &otilde;ppevormis &otilde;ppiv &otilde;pilane v&otilde;i &uuml;likooli v&otilde;i rakendusk&otilde;rgkooli statsionaarses &otilde;ppevormis &otilde;ppiv &uuml;li&otilde;pilane) v&otilde;i sellest east vanem, kui ta on tunnistatud p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks enne 18-aastaseks (p&auml;evases v&otilde;i statsionaarses &otilde;ppevormis &otilde;ppija enne 24-aastaseks) saamist. </eesti>
<inglise>1) a child, brother, sister or grandchild who is under 18 years of age (or who is under 24 years of age and is a student enrolled in daytime study at an upper secondary school or vocational educational institution or a student enrolled in full-time study at a university or institution of applied higher education), or who is older if he or she was declared permanently incapacitated for work before he or she attained 18 years of age (or in the case of a student enrolled in daytime or full-time study, before he or she attained 24 years of age). </inglise>
<eesti>Vennal, &otilde;el v&otilde;i lapselapsel on &otilde;igus pensionile siis, kui tal ei ole t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imelisi vanemaid; </eesti>
<inglise>A brother, sister or grandchild has the right to receive a pension if he or she does not have parents with capacity for work; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.01.99 j&otilde;ust. 23.01.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 150; 08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857; 15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.01.99 entered into force 23.01.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 150; 08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857; 15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>2) pensionieas v&otilde;i p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu vanem v&otilde;i lesk, kelle abielu toitjaga oli kestnud v&auml;hemalt viis aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a parent who is of pensionable age or permanently incapacitated for work, or a widow or widower who is of pensionable age or permanently incapacitated for work whose marriage to the provider had a duration of at least five years; </inglise>
<eesti>3) lahutatud abikaasa, kui ta j&otilde;udis pensioniikka v&otilde;i tunnistati p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks enne abielu lahutamist v&otilde;i enne kolme aasta m&ouml;&ouml;dumist abielu lahutamisest, kui abielu oli kestnud v&auml;hemalt 25 aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a divorced spouse if he or she attained pensionable age or was declared permanently incapacitated for work before the divorce, or within three years after the divorce if the marriage had a duration of at least twenty-five years; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &uuml;ks vanematest, lesk v&otilde;i eestkostja, kes ei t&ouml;&ouml;ta ning kasvatab toitja alla 14-aastast last, venda, &otilde;de v&otilde;i lapselast oma perekonnas. </eesti>
<inglise>4) one parent, or the widow, widower or guardian who is not employed and is raising a child, brother, sister or grandchild of the provider who is under 14 years of age in his or her family. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 loetletud isikutele m&auml;&auml;ratakse toitjakaotuspension, kui toitjal oli surma p&auml;evaks pensioni&otilde;iguslik v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;, mis oleks olnud vajalik temale t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni m&auml;&auml;ramiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Persons listed in subsection (3) of this section shall be granted a survivor's pension if the provider has by the date of his or her death completed the years of pensionable service or acquired the accumulation period which would have been necessary for the grant of a pension for incapacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud tingimustel on &otilde;igus toitjakaotuspensionile samuti: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Under the conditions provided for in this section, the following also have the right to receive a survivor's pension: </inglise>
<eesti>1) v&otilde;&otilde;raslapsel v&otilde;i kasulapsel, kelle v&otilde;&otilde;rasvanem v&otilde;i kasuvanem on surnud ja kes ei saa elatist oma vanemalt; </eesti>
<inglise>1) stepchildren and foster-children whose step-parents or foster parents are dead and who are not maintained by their parents; </inglise>
<eesti>2) v&otilde;&otilde;rasvanemal v&otilde;i kasuvanemal, kes on v&otilde;&otilde;raslast v&otilde;i kasulast kasvatanud ja &uuml;lal pidanud v&auml;hemalt kaheksa aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>2) step-parents and foster parents who have raised and maintained stepchildren or foster-children for at least eight years. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esolevat seadust kohaldatakse toitjakaotuspensioni m&auml;&auml;ramiseks ka siis, kui toitja on kehtestatud korras tunnistatud teadmata kadunuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) This Act also applies to the grant of a survivor's pension if the provider is declared missing pursuant to established procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Toitjakaotuspension m&auml;&auml;ratakse ajaks, mil isik vastab selle pensioni saamiseks k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis etten&auml;htud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A survivor's pension shall be granted for the period during which a person meets the requirements prescribed in this section for receiving a pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) P&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu isik loetakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 3 t&auml;henduses toitjakaotuspensionile &otilde;igust omavaks perekonnaliikmeks juhul, kui tal on &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensionile v&otilde;i p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse alusel rahvapensionile. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) A person who is permanently incapacitated for work is deemed to be a family member with the right to receive a survivor's pension within the meaning of subsection (3) of this section, if he or she has the right to receive a pension for incapacity for work or a national pension on the basis of permanent incapacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Toitjakaotuspensioni arvutamise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications of calculation of survivor's pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Toitjakaotuspensioni arvutamise aluseks v&otilde;etakse suurem j&auml;rgnevatest: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The greatest of the following shall be the basis for calculation of a survivor's pension: </inglise>
<eesti>1) toitja surmap&auml;evani omandatud pensioni&otilde;igusliku ja pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i alusel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 21 ja 22 s&auml;tete kohaselt arvutatud pension; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the pension calculated on the basis of the years of pensionable service and accumulation period acquired by the person until the date of his or her death pursuant to the provisions of &sect;&sect; 21 and 22 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vanaduspension 30-aastase pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i korral. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the old-age pension if the person has completed thirty years of pensionable service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Toitjakaotuspension arvutatakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 alusel arvutatud pensionist j&auml;rgmistes m&auml;&auml;rades: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A survivor's pension shall be calculated based on the pension calculated pursuant to subsection (1) of this section at the following rates: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;hele perekonnaliikmele 40 protsenti; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to one family member, 40 per cent; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kahele perekonnaliikmele 70 protsenti; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to two family members, 70 per cent; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kolmele v&otilde;i enamale perekonnaliikmele 100 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>3) to three or more family members, 100 per cent. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Rahvapension </eesti>
<inglise>National Pension </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus rahvapensionile </eesti>
<inglise>Right to receive national pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahvapension m&auml;&auml;ratakse isikule, kellel ei ole &otilde;igust vanadus-, t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus- v&otilde;i toitjakaotuspensionile n&otilde;utava pensioni&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i puudumise t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A national pension shall be granted to persons who do not have the right to receive an old-age pension, pension for incapacity for work or survivor's pension because they have not completed a sufficient number of years of pensionable service or their accumulation period is insufficient. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;igus rahvapensionile on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following have the right to receive a national pension: </inglise>
<eesti>1) (Kehtetu - 08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>1) (Repealed - 08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>2) 63-aastaseks saanud isikul, kellel ei ole &otilde;igust teist liiki pensionile ja kes on elanud Eestis alalise elanikuna v&otilde;i t&auml;htajalise elamisloa alusel v&auml;hemalt viis aastat enne pensioni taotlemist, kui ta ei saa m&otilde;ne teise riigi pensioni; </eesti>
<inglise>2) persons who have attained 63 years of age who do not have the right to receive another class of pension and who have been permanent residents of Estonia or have resided in Estonia on the basis of a temporary residence permit for at least five years before making a pension claim, if they do not receive a pension from another state; </inglise>
<eesti>3) p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isikul, kelle t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotuse protsent on v&auml;hemalt 40 ja kellel puudub t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni m&auml;&auml;ramiseks n&otilde;utav pensioni&otilde;iguslik v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;, kui ta ei saa m&otilde;ne teise riigi pensioni; </eesti>
<inglise>3) persons who are declared permanently incapacitated for work, the percentage of whose loss of capacity for work is at least 40 and who have not completed a sufficient number of years of pensionable service or whose accumulation period is insufficient for the grant of a pension for incapacity for work, if they do not receive a pension from another state; </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>4) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 13 nimetatud isikul, kellel seoses toitjal n&otilde;utava pensioni&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i puudumisega ei ole &otilde;igust toitjakaotuspensionile, kui ta ei saa m&otilde;ne teise riigi pensioni; </eesti>
<inglise>4) persons specified in &sect; 13 of this Act who, in connection with the insufficient number of years of pensionable service or the insufficient accumulation period of their providers, do not have the right to receive a survivor's pension, if they do not receive a pension from another state; </inglise>
<eesti>5) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioniikka j&otilde;udnud isikul, kellele maksti p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse alusel rahvapensioni kuni vanaduspensionieani v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 50 l&otilde;ike 2 alusel endises suuruses s&auml;ilitatud pensioni kuni m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajani. </eesti>
<inglise>5) persons who have attained a pensionable age provided for in subsections 7 (1) or (2) of this Act who are paid the national pension based on incapacity for work until the persons attain a pensionable age or the pension retained in the former amount for a specified term pursuant to subsection 50 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 alusel m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahvapension j&auml;rgmiseks t&auml;htajaks: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A national pension shall be granted pursuant to subsection (2) of this section for the following terms: </inglise>
<eesti>1) punktides 2 ja 5 nimetatud isikutele eluajaks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to persons specified in clauses 2) and 5) for life; </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857; 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857; 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>2) punktis 3 nimetatud isikule p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ajaks, kuid mitte kauemaks kui vanaduspensionieani; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to persons specified in clause 3), for the period of permanent incapacity for work but for not longer than until the age for an old-age pension is attained; </inglise>
<eesti>3) punktis 4 nimetatud isikule ajaks, mil ta vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 13 etten&auml;htud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>3) to persons specified in clause 4), for the period during which they meet the requirements prescribed in &sect; 13 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Rahvapensioni suurus </eesti>
<inglise>Amount of national pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;ra kehtestab Riigikogu riigieelarve vastuv&otilde;tmisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The national pension rate shall be established by the Riigikogu (2) upon passage of the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahvapension m&auml;&auml;ratakse j&auml;rgmistes suurustes: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A national pension shall be granted in the following amounts: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 15 l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 2 ja 5 nimetatud isikule 100 protsenti rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to persons specified in clauses 15 (2) 2) and 5) of this Act, 100 per cent of the national pension rate; </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857; 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857; 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 15 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 3 nimetatud isikule t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotusele vastav protsent rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to persons specified in clause 15 (2) 3) of this Act, a percentage of the rate of national pension corresponding to the loss of the person's capacity for work; </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>3) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 15 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 4 nimetatud isikule kolme v&otilde;i enama perekonnaliikme korral 100 protsenti, kahe perekonnaliikme korral 70 protsenti ja &uuml;he perekonnaliikme korral 40 protsenti rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>3) to persons specified in clause 15 (2) 4) of this Act, 100 per cent of the national pension rate in the case of three or more family members, 70 per cent of the national pension rate in the case of two family members and 40 per cent of the national pension rate in the case of one family member. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Pensionilisad </eesti>
<inglise>Pension Supplements </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus pensionilisale </eesti>
<inglise>Right to receive pension supplements </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vanadus- ja t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensionile arvutatakse juurde j&auml;rgmised pensionilisad: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following pension supplements shall be added to old-age pensions and pensions for incapacity for work: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Vabaduss&otilde;jast osav&otilde;tnule 100 protsenti rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) 100 per cent of the national pension rate to participants in the Estonian War of Independence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kaitsev&auml;eteenistuses teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel v&otilde;i seoses teenistuskohustustega saadud vigastuse v&otilde;i sellega seotud haiguse t&otilde;ttu t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotuse protsendiga v&auml;hemalt 40 protsenti p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isikule 25 protsenti rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast; </eesti>
<inglise>2) 25 per cent of the national pension rate to persons declared permanently incapacitated for work due to injury or illness related to injury upon the performance of duties in the service of the armed forces if the percentage of the loss of their capacity for work is at least 40 per cent; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>3) tuumakatastroofi, tuumakatsetuse, samuti aatomielektrijaama avarii tagaj&auml;rjel t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotuse protsendiga v&auml;hemalt 40 protsenti p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isikule 10 protsenti rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast; </eesti>
<inglise>3) 10 per cent of the national pension rate to persons declared permanently incapacitated for work as a result of a nuclear disaster, nuclear test, or an accident at a nuclear power station if the percentage of the loss of their capacity for work is at least 40 per cent; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>4) II maailmas&otilde;jast osav&otilde;tnule v&otilde;i Omakaitse liikmele 10 protsenti rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast; </eesti>
<inglise>4) 10 per cent of the national pension rate to participants in the Second World War or members of the Self-Defence Force; </inglise>
<eesti>5) Vabaduss&otilde;jast osav&otilde;tnu lesele 100 protsenti rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>5) 100 per cent of the national pension rate to widows and widowers of participants in the Estonian War of Independence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-4 etten&auml;htud pensionilisa arvutatakse juurde ka nimetatud punktides loetletud isikute perekonnale m&auml;&auml;ratud toitjakaotuspensionile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The pension supplements prescribed in clauses (1) 1) -4) of this section shall also be added to survivor's pensions granted to the families of persons listed in those clauses. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 5 etten&auml;htud pensionilisa arvutatakse juurde ka toitjakaotuspensioni saajale, kes vastab nimetatud lisa saamise tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The pension supplement prescribed in clause (1) 5) of this section shall also be added to the pensions of recipients of survivor's pensions who meet the requirements for receiving that supplement. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Rehabiliteeritud isiku v&otilde;i s&otilde;javangis v&otilde;i II maailmas&otilde;ja ajal koonduslaagris, getos, samuti aastatel 1941-1942 t&ouml;&ouml;- ja ehituspataljonis v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;- ja ehituskolonnis viibinud isiku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensionile arvutatakse juurde pensionilisa 20 protsenti rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A pension supplement of 20 per cent of the national pension rate shall be added to pensions for incapacity for work of rehabilitated persons, persons held as prisoners of war, and persons held in concentration camps or ghettos during the Second World War or in labour and construction battalions or labour and construction units in 1941-1942. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Isikule, kellel on &otilde;igus mitmele k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis loetletud pensionilisale, makstakse &uuml;ks pensionilisa tema valikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Persons who have the right to receive several of the pension supplements listed in this section shall be granted one pension supplement of their choice. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) (Kehtetu - 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(6) (Repealed - 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Pensioni&otilde;iguslik staa&zcaron; </eesti>
<inglise>Years of Pensionable Service </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i hulka arvatava tegevuse aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Time included in years of pensionable service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i hulka arvatakse tegevuse aeg, kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja oli kohustatud maksma sotsiaalmaksu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Time during which an employer is required to pay social tax shall be included in the years of pensionable service of a person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i hulka arvatakse samuti: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Years of pensionable service shall also include: </inglise>
<eesti>1) loomeliitude ja kutse&uuml;hingute liikmete tegevuse aeg alates loometegevuse algusest. </eesti>
<inglise>1) time during which a person is a member of an artistic association or trade union as of the time the person begins engaging in creative activity. </inglise>
<eesti>1991. aasta 1. jaanuarist arvatakse nimetatud isikute loometegevuse aeg staa&zcaron;i hulka juhul, kui maksti sotsiaalmaksu; </eesti>
<inglise>As of 1 January 1991, time during which a person was or is engaged in creative activity shall be included in their length of service if social tax was or is paid; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teenistusaeg Eesti kaitsev&auml;es ning koosk&otilde;las kaitsev&auml;eteenistuse seadusega (RT I 1994, 23, 384; 1995, 18, 240; 62, 1056; 1996, 25, 519; 49, 953; 1997, 95/96, 1575) nimetatud teenistusega v&otilde;rdsustatud teenistusaeg, samuti teenistusaeg Siseministeeriumi s&uuml;steemis; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the period of service of a person in the armed forces of Estonia, any period of service deemed to be equal thereto in accordance with the Armed Forces Service Act (RT I 1994, 23, 384; 1995, 18, 240; 62, 1056; 1996, 25, 519; 49, 953; 1997, 95/96, 1575), and any period of service in the employment of the Ministry of Internal Affairs; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kohustusliku s&otilde;jav&auml;eteenistuse ja asendusteenistuse aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>3) time during which a person is in compulsory military service or compulsory alternative service; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &otilde;piaeg kutse&otilde;ppeasutuse p&auml;evases &otilde;ppevormis v&otilde;i &uuml;likooli v&otilde;i rakendusk&otilde;rgkooli statsionaarses &otilde;ppevormis v&otilde;i nendega v&otilde;rdsustatud &otilde;ppevormides; </eesti>
<inglise>4) time during which a person is enrolled in daytime study at a vocational educational institution, in full-time study at a university or institution of applied higher education, or in a form of study deemed to be equal thereto; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.01.99 j&otilde;ust. 23.01.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 150) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.01.1999 entered into force 23.01.1999 - RT I 1999, 10, 150) </inglise>
<eesti>5) diplomaadi abikaasa v&auml;lisesinduses oleku aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>5) time during which the spouse of a diplomat is in a foreign mission; </inglise>
<eesti>6) I grupi invaliidi, lapsinvaliidi, alla 18-aastase lapseeast invaliidi eest hoolitsemise aeg ning emale, isale, v&otilde;&otilde;rasvanemale, eestkostjale v&otilde;i lapse tegelikule hooldajale v&auml;ikelapse eest hoolitsemise aeg kuni lapse 3-aastaseks saamiseni; </eesti>
<inglise>6) time during which a person cares for a Category I disabled person, a disabled child or a person under 18 years of age who is disabled since childhood, and time during which a mother, father, step-patent, guardian or actual caregiver of the child cares for a child under 3 years of age until the child attains 3 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>7) riigi t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivetalituses t&ouml;&ouml;tu abiraha saamise v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivetalituse vahendusel t&ouml;&ouml;turukoolituses osalemise aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>7) time during which a person receives unemployment benefit in a state employment office or participates in employment training organised by an employment office; </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>8) t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aeg kirikus (koguduses) v&otilde;i muus registreeritud usuorganisatsioonis. </eesti>
<inglise>8) time during which a person works in a church (congregation) or other registered religious organisation. </inglise>
<eesti>1991. aasta 1. jaanuarist arvatakse nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aeg staa&zcaron;i hulka juhul, kui maksti sotsiaalmaksu; </eesti>
<inglise>As of 1 January 1991, such time shall be included in the length of service if social tax was or is paid; </inglise>
<eesti>9) t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aeg talus enne talu likvideerimist, kolhoosi, sovhoosi v&otilde;i mujale t&ouml;&ouml;le asumist, kui isik oli v&auml;hemalt 14 aastat vana; </eesti>
<inglise>9) time during which a person worked on a farm before its liquidation or before commencing work on a collective farm, state farm or elsewhere, if the person was at least 14 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>10) t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aeg talus, kui koosk&otilde;las Eesti NSV taluseadusega (ENSV Teataja 1989, 39, 611; RT I 1993, 72/73, 1021; 1994, 30, 465; 66, 1159) oli talu maksude maksmisest vabastatud; </eesti>
<inglise>10) time during which a person worked on a farm, if the farm was exempt from taxes in accordance with the Estonian SSR Farm Act (ENSV Teataja (3) 1989, 39, 611; RT I 1993, 72/73, 1021; 1994, 30, 465; 66, 1159); </inglise>
<eesti>11) &uuml;hele vanematest v&otilde;i v&otilde;&otilde;rasvanemale v&otilde;i eestkostjale v&otilde;i peres hooldajale kaks aastat iga lapse kohta, keda ta on kasvatanud v&auml;hemalt kaheksa aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>11) for one parent or a step-parent or guardian or caregiver in a family, two years for every child whom he or she has raised for at least eight years; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>12) Eesti Vabariigi territooriumil v&otilde;&otilde;rriikide okupatsiooni vastases relvastatud vabadusv&otilde;itluses osalenud v&otilde;i ennast &otilde;igusvastaste repressioonide eest varjanud isiku vabadusv&otilde;itluses osalemise v&otilde;i enese varjamise aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>12) in the case of a person who participated in the armed fight for freedom against foreign occupation in the territory of the Republic of Estonia or was in hiding from unlawful repression, the time during which the person participated in the fight for freedom or was in hiding; </inglise>
<eesti>13) t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aeg f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjana, kui maksti sotsiaalmaksu; </eesti>
<inglise>13) time during which a person works as a sole proprietor if social tax was or is paid; </inglise>
<eesti>14) aeg, mil t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 13 nimetatud f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja oli ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu. </eesti>
<inglise>14) time during which an employee or sole proprietor specified in clause 13) of this subsection is temporarily incapacitated for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Sooduskorras arvatakse pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i hulka: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following shall be included in the years of pensionable service under favourable conditions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) rehabiliteeritud isiku &otilde;igusvastaselt vahi all, kinnipidamiskohas v&otilde;i asumisel oleku aeg kolmekordselt; </eesti>
<inglise>1) time a rehabilitated person spent while unlawfully in custody, in a penal institution or in exile, multiplied by three; </inglise>
<eesti>2) s&otilde;javangis, II maailmas&otilde;ja ajal koonduslaagris, getos, samuti aastatel 1941-1942 t&ouml;&ouml;- ja ehituspataljonis v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;- ja ehituskolonnis viibimise aeg kolmekordselt; </eesti>
<inglise>2) time a person spent held as a prisoner of war, or in a concentration camp or ghetto during the Second World War, or in a labour and construction battalion or labour and construction unit in 1941-1942, multiplied by three; </inglise>
<eesti>3) rehabiliteeritud isiku puhul vahi alt, kinnipidamiskohast v&otilde;i asumiselt vabanemisele j&auml;rgnenud aeg kuni Eestisse elama asumise &otilde;iguse andmiseni, kui isikult oli &otilde;igusvastaselt v&otilde;etud &otilde;igus asuda elama Eestisse, pooleteisekordselt; </eesti>
<inglise>3) time from when a rehabilitated person was freed from custody or a penal institution or returned from exile until he or she is granted the permission to settle in Estonia, if the right to live in Estonia was taken away from the person unlawfully, multiplied by one and a half; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>4) pidalit&otilde;bilas v&otilde;i katkut&otilde;rjeasutuses t&ouml;&ouml;tamise aeg kahekordselt; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the duration of employment in a leper house or institution for plague control, multiplied by two; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>5) 1944. aasta oktoobris v&otilde;i novembris Saaremaalt S&otilde;rve poolsaarelt Saksamaale sunniviisiliselt &uuml;mberasustatud isiku puhul aeg alates &uuml;mberasustamisest kuni Eestisse elama asumiseni, kuid mitte kauem kui 1946. aasta 31. detsembrini, kolmekordselt. </eesti>
<inglise>5) in the case of a person who was subject to forced displacement from S&otilde;rve peninsula in Saaremaa to Germany in October or November 1944, the time from displacement until settling in Estonia, but not longer than until 31 December 1946, multiplied by three. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i hulka arvatakse k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud tegevus endise NSV Liidu territooriumil kuni 1991. aasta 1. jaanuarini juhul, kui isikul on v&auml;hemalt 15 aastat Eestis omandatud pensioni&otilde;iguslikku v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Activities provided for in this section which took place in the territory of the former Union of Soviet Socialist Republics up to 1 January 1991 shall be included in the years of pensionable service if the person has completed at least fifteen years of pensionable service in Estonia or the accumulation period of the person acquired in Estonia is at least fifteen years. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud pensioni&otilde;iguslikku staa&zcaron;i arvestatakse kuni 1998. aasta 31. detsembrini. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The years of pensionable service provided for in this section shall be taken into account until 31 December 1998. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i arvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of years of pensionable service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Pensioni&otilde;iguslik staa&zcaron; arvutatakse t&auml;isaastates. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Pensionable service is calculated in full years. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;isaastani &uuml;mardatakse staa&zcaron;, mille pikkus on v&auml;hemalt kuus kuud, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 toodud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>If the length of service is at least six months, it shall be rounded to a full year, except in the cases specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vanadus-, t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus- v&otilde;i toitjakaotuspensionile &otilde;igust andva staa&zcaron;i kindlakstegemisel l&auml;htutakse &uuml;mardamata pensioni&otilde;iguslikust staa&zcaron;ist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Calculation of the length of service which grants the right to receive an old-age pension, pension for incapacity for work or survivor's pension is based on unrounded years of pensionable service. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i t&otilde;endamise juhendi kinnitab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Government of the Republic shall approve the instructions for certification of years of pensionable service. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i arvestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of Accumulation Period </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i arvestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of accumulation period </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i arvestamise aluseks on andmed pensionikindlustatu poolt v&otilde;i tema eest makstud v&otilde;i arvestatud sotsiaalmaksu (edaspidi isikustatud sotsiaalmaks) kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Calculation of an accumulation period shall be based on information concerning social tax paid or calculated by or for an assured person (hereinafter individually registered social tax). </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;igus pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i &uuml;hele aastale on pensionikindlustatul, kes ise on maksnud v&otilde;i kelle eest on vastavalt sotsiaalmaksuseadusele arvestatud sotsiaalmaksu v&auml;hemalt kuupalga alamm&auml;&auml;ra aastasummalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An assured person who has paid social tax himself or herself or for whom social tax has been calculated pursuant to the Social Tax Act in an amount equal to at least the minimum monthly wage for a year has the right to one year towards his or her accumulation period. </inglise>
<eesti>Isiku puhul, kelle eest sotsiaalmaksu maksab riik vastavalt sotsiaalmaksu seaduse &sect;-le 6, arvestatakse pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i samav&auml;&auml;rselt sotsiaalmaksu tasumisega kuupalga alamm&auml;&auml;ralt. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of a person for whom the state pays social tax pursuant to &sect; 6 of the Social Tax Act, the accumulation period shall be calculated to be equivalent to payment of social tax on the minimum monthly wage. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(2 (1)) Pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i arvutamisel v&otilde;rreldakse pensionikindlustatu iga kalendriaasta isikustatud sotsiaalmaksu vastava aasta jaanuarikuu kaheteistk&uuml;mnekordselt kuupalga alamm&auml;&auml;ralt arvutatud sotsiaalmaksuga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2 (1)) Upon calculation of the accumulation period, the individually registered social tax of an assured person for each calendar year shall be compared to the social tax calculated on the minimum monthly wage for January of the corresponding year multiplied by twelve. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i arvestamise juhendi kinnitab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Government of the Republic shall approve the instructions for calculation of accumulation periods. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Uuml;he kalendriaasta kohta arvestatakse kuni &uuml;ks aasta pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Up to one year per calendar year shall count towards an accumulation period. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>9. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 9 </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni arvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of State Pension </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensioni koostisosad ja pensioni arvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Components and calculation of pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklik pension, v&auml;lja arvatud rahvapension, koosneb kolmest osast: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A state pension, with the exception of a national pension, consists of three components: </inglise>
<eesti>1) baasosast, mille suuruse kehtestab Riigikogu riigieelarve vastuv&otilde;tmisel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a base amount, the amount of which shall be established by the Riigikogu upon passage of the state budget; </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>2) staa&zcaron;iosakust, mille suurus v&otilde;rdub pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i aastate arvu ja staa&zcaron;iaasta hinde korrutisega. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a component calculated on the basis of years of pensionable service, the amount of which equals the number of years of pensionable service multiplied by the value of a year of pensionable service. </inglise>
<eesti>Staa&zcaron;iaasta hinde kinnitab Vabariigi Valitsus l&auml;htuvalt riigieelarvega m&auml;&auml;ratud riikliku pensionikindlustuse kuludest ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 26 s&auml;testatud kulude jaotuse arvestusest; </eesti>
<inglise>The Government of the Republic shall approve the value of a year of pensionable service on the basis of the expenditure prescribed for state pension insurance in the state budget and the distribution of expenditure provided for in &sect; 26 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>3) kindlustusosakust, mille suurus v&otilde;rdub pensionikindlustatu aastakoefitsientide summa ja aastakoefitsiendi hinde korrutisega. </eesti>
<inglise>3) an insurance component, the amount of which equals the sum of the annual factors of an assured person multiplied by the value of the annual factor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui pensioni taotlejal ei ole pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i, m&auml;&auml;ratakse riiklik pension k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud osade alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a pension claimant has not earned an accumulation period, a state pension shall be granted on the basis of the components provided for in clauses (1) 1) and 2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Rahvapension arvutatakse protsentides rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A national pension shall be calculated as a percentage of the national pension rate. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Isikule, kellele v&auml;hemalt 15-aastase pensioni&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i korral arvutatud vanaduspensioni suurus osutub v&auml;iksemaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 16 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 1 s&auml;testatud rahvapensioni suurusest, makstakse vanaduspensioni suuruses 100 protsenti rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An old-age pension in the amount of 100% of the national pension rate shall be paid to persons whose old-age pension calculated on the basis of at least 15 years of pensionable service or an accumulation period of at least 15 years proves to be smaller than the national pension provided for in clause 16 (2) 1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Isikule, kellel puudub pensioni m&auml;&auml;ramiseks n&otilde;utav k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud pensioni&otilde;iguslik v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;, kuid kellel tekib &otilde;igus pensionile vastavalt v&auml;lislepingule, arvutatakse pension Eestis omandatud pensioni&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The pension of persons who have not completed the number of years of pensionable service or acquired the accumulation period provided for in this Act to be granted a pension, but who have the right to a pension according to an international agreement, shall be calculated on the basis of the pensionable service in Estonia or the accumulation period acquired in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellise isiku pensioni baasosa arvutamisel korrutatakse pensioni baasosa suurus Eestis omandatud pensioni&otilde;igusliku ja pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i aastate arvuga ning jagatakse viieteistk&uuml;mnega. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon calculation of the base amount of a pension for such persons, the amount of the base amount of the pension shall be multiplied by the number of years of pensionable service and accumulation period acquired in Estonia and shall be divided by fifteen. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensionikindlustatu aastakoefitsiendi ja kindlustusosaku arvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of annual factor and insurance component of assured person </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Pensionikindlustatu aastakoefitsiendi arvutamiseks liidetakse pensionikindlustatu kohta riikliku pensionikindlustuse registris arvestatud isikustatud sotsiaalmaksu summad ning jagatakse riikliku pensionikindlustuse registrisse kantud isikustatud sotsiaalmaksu keskmise suurusega antud kalendriaastal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to calculate the annual factor of an assured person, the amounts of individually registered social tax calculated for the assured person in the state pension insurance register shall be totalled and divided by the average amount of individually registered social tax entered in the state pension insurance register in the given calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pensionikindlustuse aastakoefitsiendi hinde kinnitamisel l&auml;htub Vabariigi Valitsus allj&auml;rgnevast: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Government of the Republic shall approve the value of pension insurance annual factors on the basis of the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Sotsiaalkindlustusameti koostatud prognoos pensionikindlustuse aastakoefitsientide kogusumma kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a forecast prepared by the Social Insurance Board concerning the total of the pension insurance annual factors; </inglise>
<eesti>2) riigieelarvega m&auml;&auml;ratud riikliku pensionikindlustuse kuludest ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 26 s&auml;testatud kulude jaotuse arvestusest etten&auml;htud kulud kindlustusosakute maksmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the expenditure prescribed for payment of insurance components in the expenditure prescribed for state pension insurance in the state budget and distribution of expenditure provided for in &sect; 26 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juhendi kindlustusosaku suuruse arvutamiseks kinnitab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Instructions for calculation of the amount of insurance components shall be approved by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Vabariigi Valitsus kinnitab j&auml;rgmise aasta riikliku pensionikindlustuse registrisse kantava isikustatud sotsiaalmaksu arvestusliku keskmise suuruse hiljemalt 10 kalendrip&auml;eva enne kalendriaasta algust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Government of the Republic shall approve the average amount of individually registered social tax to be entered in the state pension insurance register for the next year at least ten calendar days before the start of the calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Eelmise aasta isikustatud sotsiaalmaksu keskmise suuruse kinnitab Vabariigi Valitsus mitte hiljem kui jooksva aasta 20. m&auml;rtsil ning seda rakendatakse pensioni m&auml;&auml;ramisel ja &uuml;mberarvutamisel t&auml;htajaga alates 1. aprillist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Government of the Republic shall approve the average amount of individually registered social tax of the previous year not later than on 20 March of the current year and this shall be implemented in the grant and recalculation of pensions for a term commencing on 1 April. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui pension m&auml;&auml;ratakse tagasiulatuvalt algt&auml;htajaga enne 1. aprilli, v&otilde;etakse pensioni arvutamisel aluseks Vabariigi Valitsuse kinnitatud riikliku pensionikindlustuse registrisse kantava isikustatud sotsiaalmaksu arvestuslik keskmine suurus. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If a pension is granted retroactively with a commencement date before 1 April, the average amount of individually registered social tax approved by the Government of the Republic for entry in the state pension register shall be taken as the basis for calculation of the pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>10. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 10 </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensionikindlustuse vahendid </eesti>
<inglise>State Pension Insurance Funds </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensionikindlustuse vahendid </eesti>
<inglise>State pension insurance funds </inglise>
<eesti>Vahendid riikliku pensionikindlustuse finantseerimiseks n&auml;hakse ette igaaastases riigieelarves. </eesti>
<inglise>Funds for financing state pension insurance shall be prescribed in the annual state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensionikindlustuse kulude katteallikad </eesti>
<inglise>Sources for covering expenditure prescribed for state pension insurance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riikliku pensionikindlustuse kulude katteallikateks riigieelarves on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The sources for covering expenditure prescribed for state pension insurance in the state budget are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) sotsiaalmaks vastavalt sotsiaalmaksuseadusele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) social tax pursuant to the Social Tax Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) distsiplinaartrahv vastavalt t&ouml;&ouml;tajate distsiplinaarvastutuse seadusele (RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 16, 228; 1998, 64/65, 1009; 2000, 102, 674); </eesti>
<inglise>2) disciplinary fines pursuant to the Employees Disciplinary Punishments Act (RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 16, 228; 1998, 64/65, 1009; 2000, 102, 674); </inglise>
<eesti>3) sihtotstarbelised omatulud (intressid, dividendid, regresshagidena tagastatavad summad jm); </eesti>
<inglise>3) own revenue intended for specific purposes (interest, dividends, amounts returned in recourse actions etc); </inglise>
<eesti>4) eraldised eelmiste aastate vabadest vahenditest; </eesti>
<inglise>4) allocations from reserves from previous years; </inglise>
<eesti>5) riigieelarves etten&auml;htud muud vahendid. </eesti>
<inglise>5) other funds allocated from the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riikliku pensionikindlustuse kulude katteallikatena laekuvad tulud on selle eelarveaasta tulud, millal nad eelarvesse laekuvad, olenemata sellest, millise aasta eest nad on arvestatud v&otilde;i millal nad oleksid pidanud laekuma. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Revenue received as a source for covering expenditure prescribed for state pension insurance is included in the revenue of the budgetary year in which it is received into the budget, regardless of the year for which it is calculated or in which it should be received. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensionikindlustuse kulud </eesti>
<inglise>Expenditure prescribed for state pension insurance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 24 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-4 nimetatud riikliku pensionikindlustuse kulude katteallikate arvel finantseeritakse &uuml;ksnes j&auml;rgmised kulud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Only the following expenditure shall be financed out of the sources for covering expenditure prescribed for state pension insurance specified in clauses 24 (1) 1) -4) of this Act: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&auml;esoleva seadusega s&auml;testatud vanaduspensionid, t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensionid, toitjakaotuspensionid, rahvapensionid ja endises suuruses s&auml;ilitatud pensionid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) old-age pensions, pensions for incapacity for work, survivor's pensions, national pensions and pensions retained in their former amounts provided for in this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) v&auml;ljateenitud aastate pensionide seaduses (RT 1992, 21, 294; RT I 1993, 40, 596; 1994, 24, 398; 51, 856; 83, 1450; 1995, 61, 1027; 95, 1631; 1996, 22, 437; 86, 1539; 1997, 81, 1366; 1998, 17, 266; 107, 1767; 2000, 25, 147; 28, 167; 58, 376) ja soodustingimustel vanaduspensionide seaduses (RT 1992, 21, 292; RT I 1993, 40, 596; 1994, 24, 398; 51, 856; 83, 1450; 1995, 61, 1027; 95, 1631; 1996, 22, 437; 86, 1539; 1997, 81, 1366; 1998, 17, 266; 107, 1767; 2000, 25, 147; 28, 167; 58, 376) s&auml;testatud pensionid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) pensions provided for in the Superannuated Pensions Act (RT 1992, 21, 294; RT I 1993, 40, 596; 1994, 24, 398; 51, 856; 83, 1450; 1995, 61, 1027; 95, 1631; 1996, 22, 437; 86, 1539; 1997, 81, 1366; 1998, 17, 266; 107, 1767; 2000, 25, 147; 28, 167; 58, 376) and the Old-Age Pensions under Favourable Conditions Act (RT 1992, 21, 292; RT I 1993, 40, 596; 1994, 24, 398; 51, 856; 83, 1450; 1995, 61, 1027; 95, 1631; 1996, 22, 437; 86, 1539; 1997, 81, 1366; 1998, 17, 266; 107, 1767; 2000, 25, 147; 28, 167; 58, 376); </inglise>
<eesti>3) pensionide v&auml;ljamaksmise panga- ja postikulud. </eesti>
<inglise>3) bank charges and postage of payment of pensions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 24 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 5 nimetatud vahendite arvel finantseeritakse j&auml;rgmised k&auml;esolevast seadusest tulenevad kulud: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following expenditure arising from this Act shall be financed out of funds specified in clause 24 (1) 5) of this Act: </inglise>
<eesti>1) paragrahvi 9 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud soodustingimustel vanaduspensionid kuni isiku &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioniikka j&otilde;udmiseni; </eesti>
<inglise>1) old-age pensions under favourable conditions provided for in subsection 9 (1) of this Act until a person attains the pensionable age provided for in subsections 7 (1) or (2); </inglise>
<eesti>2) paragrahvi 10 l&otilde;igetes 4 ja 4 (1) s&auml;testatud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensionid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) pensions for incapacity for work provided for in subsections 10 (4) and (4 (1)); </inglise>
<eesti>3) paragrahvis 17 s&auml;testatud pensionilisad; </eesti>
<inglise>3) pension supplements provided for in &sect; 17; </inglise>
<eesti>4) pensionid ja pensionilisad &sect; 18 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 12 ning l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i aastate eest; </eesti>
<inglise>4) pensions and pension supplements for the years of pensionable service specified in clause 18 (2) 12) and subsection 18 (3); </inglise>
<eesti>5) pensionikindlustatute informeerimine &sect; 35 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>5) provision of information to assured persons pursuant to &sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eesti riigi poolt m&otilde;ne muu seaduse alusel makstavaid pensione ja pensionilisasid finantseeritakse vastavates seadustes etten&auml;htud vahenditest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Pensions and pension supplements paid by Estonia pursuant to other Acts shall be financed out of funds prescribed by the corresponding Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensionikindlustuse kulude jaotuse arvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Distribution of expenditure prescribed for state pension insurance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 25 s&auml;testatud riikliku pensionikindlustuse kulude &uuml;ldmahust lahutatakse kulud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following expenditure shall be deducted from the volume of expenditure prescribed for state pension insurance provided for in &sect; 25 of this Act: </inglise>
<eesti>1) pensionilisade maksmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) expenditure for the payment of pension supplements; </inglise>
<eesti>2) rahvapensionide maksmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) expenditure for the payment of pensions; </inglise>
<eesti>3) endises suuruses s&auml;ilitatud pensionide maksmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) expenditure for the payment of pensions retained in their former amounts; </inglise>
<eesti>4) pensionide v&auml;ljamaksmise posti- ja pangakuludeks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) expenditure for bank charges and postage of payment of pensions; </inglise>
<eesti>5) pensionikindlustatute informeerimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>5) expenditure for provision of information to assured persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 alusel saadud summa v&otilde;etakse aluseks riiklike pensionide baasosa, staa&zcaron;iosaku ja kindlustusosaku maksmiseks vajalike kulude arvestamisel, l&auml;htudes j&auml;rgmistest piirm&auml;&auml;radest: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The amount calculated pursuant to subsection (1) of this section shall be the basis upon calculation of expenditure necessary for the payment of base amounts, components calculated on the basis of years of pensionable service, and insurance components of state pensions, based on the following limits: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kuni 30 protsenti nimetatud summast eraldatakse riiklike pensionide baasosa maksmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) up to 30 per cent of the specified amount shall be allocated for the payment of the base amounts of state pensions; </inglise>
<eesti>2) v&auml;hemalt 70 protsenti nimetatud summast jagatakse proportsionaalselt vastavalt pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i aastate ja pensionikindlustuse aastakoefitsientide osakaalule nende &uuml;ldarvus. </eesti>
<inglise>2) at least 70 per cent of the specified amount shall be allocated according to the proportion of years of pensionable service and the annual pension insurance factors. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui p&auml;rast riigieelarve vastuv&otilde;tmist kehtestatud seaduste alusel riikliku pensionikindlustuse kulude katteallikad v&auml;henevad v&otilde;i kulud suurenevad, s&auml;testatakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses kulude t&auml;iendavad katteallikad. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If, pursuant to Acts established after passage of the state budget, the sources for covering expenditure prescribed for state pension insurance decrease or the expenditure increases, sources of compensation for the additional expenditure shall be provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. (Kehtetu - 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. (Repealed - 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>11. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 11 </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik pensionikindlustuse register </eesti>
<inglise>State Pension Insurance Register </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Registri staatus </eesti>
<inglise>Status of register </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik pensionikindlustuse register (edaspidi register) on riiklik register andmekogude seaduse (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597) &sect; 31 t&auml;henduses, mis sisaldab andmeid pensionikindlustatute kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>The state pension insurance register (hereinafter register) is a state register as defined in &sect; 31 of the Databases Act (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597) and which contains data on assured persons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Registri eesm&auml;rk </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of register </inglise>
<eesti>Registri eesm&auml;rk on andmete tagamine Sotsiaalkindlustusametile k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja teiste seadustega pandud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The purpose of the register is to ensure the availability of data for the performance of functions imposed on the Social Insurance Board by this Act and other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Registri asutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of register </inglise>
<eesti>Registri asutab Vabariigi Valitsus sotsiaalministri ettepanekul andmekogude seadusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The register shall be established by the Government of the Republic on the proposal of the Minister of Social Affairs pursuant to the procedure established by the Databases Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Kannete tegemine registrisse ja andmete saamine registrist </eesti>
<inglise>Entries in register and receiving data from register </inglise>
<eesti>Andmete kandmine registrisse ja andmete saamine registrist toimub vastavalt andmekogude seadusele, isikuandmete kaitse seadusele (RT I 1996, 48, 944; 1998, 59, 941; 111, 1833; 2000, 50, 317; 92, 597; 104, 685), sotsiaalmaksuseadusele, k&auml;esolevale seadusele ja teistele seadustele ning riikliku pensionikindlustuse registri pidamise p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusele, mille kinnitab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>Data shall be entered in and received from the register pursuant to the Databases Act, the Personal Data Protection Act (RT I 1996, 48, 944; 1998, 59, 941; 111, 1833; 2000, 50, 317; 92, 597; 104, 685), the Social Tax Act, this Act and other Acts, and the statutes for maintenance of the state pension insurance register which shall be approved by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Registri vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja </eesti>
<inglise>Chief processor of register </inglise>
<eesti>Registri vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja on Sotsiaalkindlustusamet. </eesti>
<inglise>The chief processor of the register is the Social Insurance Board. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Andmete koosseis ja allikad </eesti>
<inglise>Composition and sources of data </inglise>
<eesti>Register sisaldab: </eesti>
<inglise>The register shall contain the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isikut identifitseerivaid andmeid, mille allikregistriks on rahvastiku arvestuse andmebaas. </eesti>
<inglise>1) data identifying persons, based on data in the population registration database. </inglise>
<eesti>Isik loetakse registrisse kantuks, kui teda identifitseerivad andmed on registrisse kantud kas rahvastiku arvestuse andmebaasi, passi v&otilde;i s&uuml;nnitunnistuse alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>A person is deemed to be entered in the register if data identifying him or her has been entered in the register on the basis of the population registration database or his or her passport or birth certificate; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isiku &uuml;ldandmeid, mille allikregistriks on rahvastiku arvestuse andmebaas; </eesti>
<inglise>2) general data concerning persons, based on data in the population registration database; </inglise>
<eesti>3) isiku sotsiaalmaksualaseid andmeid, mille allikregistriks on maksumaksjate ja maksu kinnipidajate register v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&otilde;end arvestatud ja makstud sotsiaalmaksu kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) data concerning social tax paid by or for persons, based on data in the register of taxpayers and withholding agents or certificates from employers concerning social tax calculated and paid; </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>4) andmeid pensioni m&auml;&auml;ramise ja maksmise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>4) data concerning the grant and payment of pensions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Sotsiaalmaksu, pensioni&otilde;igusliku ja pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i arvestus </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of social tax, years of pensionable service and accumulation period </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Registris peetakse arvestust isiku kohta tema poolt v&otilde;i tema eest makstud ja arvestatud sotsiaalmaksu ning pensioni&otilde;igusliku ja pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Records shall be maintained in the register concerning social tax calculated and paid by or for a person and the years of pensionable service and accumulation period of a person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Registri andmete alusel arvutatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 22 s&auml;testatud korras igale pensionikindlustatule kord aastas tema aastakoefitsient. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The annual factor of every assured person shall be calculated once a year on the basis of the data in the register pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 22 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Registri andmete alusel arvutatakse igale pensionikindlustatule tema pensionikindlustuse aastakoefitsientide summa. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The sum of a person's pension insurance annual factors shall be calculated on the basis of the data in the register for every assured person. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensionikindlustatu informeerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of assured persons </inglise>
<eesti>Kord aastas teatab register igale pensionikindlustatule tema poolt v&otilde;i tema eest makstud ja arvestatud sotsiaalmaksu summa, pensionikindlustuse aastakoefitsiendi ja pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i. </eesti>
<inglise>The register shall notify assured persons once a year of the amount of social tax calculated and paid by or for them, and their pension insurance annual factor and accumulation period. </inglise>
<eesti>12. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 12 </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni taotlemine ja m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Claim for and Grant of State Pension </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni taotlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Claim for state pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklikule pensionile &otilde;igust omav isik esitab pensioniavalduse elukohaj&auml;rgsele pensioniametile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Persons with the right to receive a state pension shall submit a pension claim to their local pension office. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riikliku pensioni taotlemiseks vajalike dokumentide vormid kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The format of the necessary documents for making a claim for a state pension shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Pensioni taotlemise p&auml;evaks loetakse p&auml;ev, millal elukohaj&auml;rgne pensioniamet v&otilde;tab vastu avalduse koos k&otilde;igi vajalike dokumentidega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The date on which a local pension office receives a claim together with all necessary documents is deemed to be the date of making a pension claim. </inglise>
<eesti>Dokumentide vastuv&otilde;tmise kohta antakse pensionitaotlejale &otilde;iend. </eesti>
<inglise>A certificate shall be issued to a pension claimant concerning receipt of the documents. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui pensionitaotlus on saadetud posti teel ning seejuures on lisatud k&otilde;ik vajalikud dokumendid, loetakse pensioni taotlemise p&auml;evaks taotluse l&auml;htekoha postitempli kuup&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a pension claim is sent by post and all necessary documents are appended, the date on the date stamp of the place in which the claim is posted is deemed to be the date of making the pension claim. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui pensionitaotlusele ei ole lisatud k&otilde;iki vajalikke dokumente, teatatakse pensioni taotlejale, arvates avalduse saabumisest k&uuml;mne t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul, missugused dokumendid tuleb esitada t&auml;iendavalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If not all the necessary documents are appended to a pension claim, the pension claimant shall be notified of the documents to be additionally submitted within ten working days after receipt of a claim. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui need esitatakse hiljemalt kolme kuu jooksul, arvates t&auml;iendavate dokumentide esitamise vajaduse kohta teatise saamise p&auml;evast, loetakse pensioni taotlemise p&auml;evaks taotluse vastuv&otilde;tmise p&auml;ev v&otilde;i taotluse l&auml;htekoha postitempli kuup&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>If such documents are submitted within three months after receipt of the notice concerning the requirement to submit additional documents, the date of receipt of the claim or the date on the date stamp of the place in which the claim is posted is deemed to be the date of making the pension claim. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of state pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riikliku pensioni m&auml;&auml;rab elukohaj&auml;rgse pensioniameti direktor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;i pensioniameti direktori poolt volitatud pensioniameti struktuuri&uuml;ksuse juht. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The director or deputy director of a local pension office or the head of a structural unit of the pension office authorised by the director of the pension office grants a state pension. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensionitaotleja n&otilde;udmisel, samuti kollegiaalset lahendust n&otilde;udva pensionitaotluse puhul otsustab pensioni m&auml;&auml;ramise pensionikomisjon, mille moodustamise ja t&ouml;&ouml;korra m&auml;&auml;rab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the request of a pension claimant, or in the case of a pension claim which requires a collegial decision, the grant of a pension shall be decided by a pension committee, the formation and procedures of which shall be determined by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pensionikomisjoni p&auml;devusse kuulub: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following are within the competence of the pension committee: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&otilde;ikide k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel tekkinud pensioni taotlemise, m&auml;&auml;ramise, &uuml;helt pensioniliigilt teisele &uuml;leviimise, pensioni &uuml;mberarvutamise ja pensioni maksmise vaidluste lahendamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) resolution of disputes arising pursuant to this Act concerning pension claims, the grant of pensions, transfers from one class of pension to another, recalculation of pensions and payment of pensions; </inglise>
<eesti>2) pensioni&otilde;igusliku staa&zcaron;i t&otilde;endamiseks esitatud dokumentidele &otilde;igusliku hinnangu andmine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) rendering legal opinions on documents submitted to certify years of pensionable service; </inglise>
<eesti>3) seadusliku aluseta m&auml;&auml;ratud pensioni maksmise l&otilde;petamine; samuti pensioni maksmise peatamine ning liigselt makstud pensionisummade pensionist kinnipidamise otsustamine. </eesti>
<inglise>3) termination of payment of pensions granted without legal basis, suspension of payment of pensions and decisions on withholding overpaid pension amounts from pensions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Elukohaj&auml;rgne pensioniamet osutab pensionitaotlejale vajadusel kaasabi pensioni taotlemiseks vajalike dokumentide saamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The local pension office shall assist the pension claimant when necessary in obtaining the necessary documents for making a pension claim. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riiklik pension m&auml;&auml;ratakse alates pensioni taotlemise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A state pension shall be granted as of the date of making a pension claim. </inglise>
<eesti>Varasemast t&auml;htajast m&auml;&auml;ratakse pension j&auml;rgmistel juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise>A pension shall be granted as of an earlier date in the following cases: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vanaduspension m&auml;&auml;ratakse pensioniikka j&otilde;udmise p&auml;evast (&sect; 7 l&otilde;iked 1 v&otilde;i 2 v&otilde;i &sect; 9 l&otilde;ige 1), t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension ning rahvapension p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isikule m&auml;&auml;ratakse p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse kindlakstegemise p&auml;evast, kui pensionitaotlus on esitatud kolme kuu jooksul, arvates pensioniikka j&otilde;udmise v&otilde;i p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse kindlakstegemise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an old-age pension shall be granted as of the date of attaining pensionable age (subsections 7 (1) or (2) or subsection 9 (1)), and a pension for incapacity for work or a national pension shall be granted to a person declared permanently incapacitated for work as of the date of determination of the permanent incapacity for work, if the pension claim is made within three months after the date of attaining pensionable age or determination of the permanent incapacity for work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) toitjakaotuspension v&otilde;i rahvapension toitja surma v&otilde;i teadmata kadunuks tunnistamise p&auml;evast, kuid mitte &uuml;le 12 kuu enne pensioni taotlemist. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a survivor's pension or national pension shall be granted as of the date of death of the provider or the declaration of a provider as missing, but not more than twelve months before making a pension claim. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Perekonnaliikmetele ja nendega v&otilde;rdsustatud isikutele, kellel on &otilde;igus saada toitjakaotuspensioni v&otilde;i rahvapensioni toitja kaotuse korral, m&auml;&auml;ratakse &uuml;hine pension. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A common pension shall be granted to family members and persons deemed to be equal to them who have the right to receive a survivor's pension or national pension upon the loss of a provider. </inglise>
<eesti>Perekonnaliikme avalduse alusel eraldatakse toitjakaotuspensionist tema osa ja makstakse see talle eraldi v&auml;lja. </eesti>
<inglise>On the basis of an application of a family member, his or her share shall be separated from the survivor's pension and paid to him or her separately. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Pension&auml;rile antakse pensionitunnistus, mille vormi m&auml;&auml;rab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Pensioners shall be granted a pension certificate, the format of which shall be determined by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensioni &uuml;mberarvutamise t&auml;htajad </eesti>
<inglise>Terms for recalculation of pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riikliku pensioni v&auml;hendamist v&otilde;i suurendamist tingivate asjaolude tekkimisel arvutatakse pension &uuml;mber. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A state pension shall be recalculated if circumstances arise which require the reduction or increase of the state pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pensioni v&auml;hendamist tingivate asjaolude tekkimisel arvutatakse pension &uuml;mber nende asjaolude tekkimise kuule j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesest p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If circumstances arise which require the reduction of a pension, the pension shall be recalculated as of the first day of the month following the month in which such circumstances arise. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Pensioni suurendamist tingivate asjaolude tekkimisel, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 39 l&otilde;ikes 1 toodud juhul, arvutatakse pension &uuml;mber vastava avalduse ja vajalike dokumentide esitamise p&auml;evast, kui avaldus ja vajalikud dokumendid on esitatud &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates pensioni suurendamist tingivate asjaolude tekkimisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If circumstances arise which require the increase of a pension, except for the case set out in subsection 39 (1) of this Act, the pension shall be recalculated as of the date of submission of a corresponding claim and necessary documents, if the claim and documents are submitted within one month after the circumstances requiring the increase of the pension arise. </inglise>
<eesti>Hilisemal avalduse ja vajalike dokumentide esitamisel arvutatakse pension &uuml;mber vastava avalduse ja vajalike dokumentide esitamise kuule j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesest kuup&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>If a claim and necessary documents are submitted later, the pension shall be recalculated as of the first day of the month following the month in which the corresponding claim and necessary documents are submitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Pension&auml;r on kohustatud k&uuml;mne p&auml;eva jooksul oma elukohaj&auml;rgsele pensioniametile kirjalikult teatama k&otilde;ikidest asjaoludest, mis toovad kaasa riikliku pensioni &uuml;mberarvutamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A pensioner is required within ten days to notify his or her local pension office in writing of all circumstances which bring about the need to recalculate his or her state pension. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni &uuml;mberarvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Recalculation of state pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) M&auml;&auml;ratud riiklik pension arvutatakse registrisse kantud eelmise aasta isikustatud sotsiaalmaksu andmete alusel &uuml;mber kord aastas alates 1. aprillist. </eesti>
<inglise>State pensions which have been granted shall be recalculated from 1 April on the basis of data which are entered in the register and which concern the individually registered social tax of the previous year. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;ra, pensioni baasosa suuruse, staa&zcaron;iaasta hinde ning aastakoefitsiendi hinde muutmisel arvutatakse k&otilde;ik pensionid &uuml;mber kord aastas alates 1. aprillist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the national pension rate, the amount of the base amount of a pension, the value of a year of pensionable service or the value of an annual factor are changed, all pensions shall be recalculated annually from 1 April. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) (Kehtetu - 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(3) (Repealed - 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>13. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 13 </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni maksmine </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of State Pension </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni maksmine </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of state pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklikku pensioni makstakse elukohaj&auml;rgse pensioniameti kaudu igakuuliselt jooksva kuu eest vastavalt pension&auml;ri soovile panka pension&auml;ri arvele v&otilde;i posti teel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A state pension shall be paid monthly for the current month through a local pension office either to the bank account of the pensioner or by post as requested by the pensioner. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riikliku pensioni k&auml;ttetoimetamine ja saatmine Eestis toimub maksja arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A state pension shall be delivered and sent in Estonia at the expense of the payer. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riikliku pensioni kandmine v&auml;lisriigis asuvasse panka pension&auml;ri arvele toimub saaja arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A state pension shall be transferred to the account of a pensioner in a bank in a foreign state at the expense of the recipient. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Rahvapensioni (v&auml;lja arvatud p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks tunnistatud isikule ning alla 18-aastasele lapsele v&otilde;i alla 24-aastasele p&auml;evases v&otilde;i statsionaarses &otilde;ppevormis &otilde;ppijale) ja toitjakaotuspensioni (v&auml;lja arvatud 18-aastasele lapsele v&otilde;i alla 24-aastasele p&auml;evases v&otilde;i statsionaarses &otilde;ppevormis &otilde;ppijale) t&ouml;&ouml;tamise korral ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A national pension shall not be paid to persons who are employed (except to persons who are declared permanently incapacitated for work, to children under 18 years of age, or to students under 24 years of age enrolled in daytime or full-time study); a survivor's pension shall not be paid to persons who are employed (except to children under 18 years of age or to students under 24 years of age enrolled in daytime or full-time study). </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ennet&auml;htaegset vanaduspensioni t&ouml;&ouml;tamise korral ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An early-retirement pension shall not be paid to persons who are employed. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni maksmine volikirja alusel </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of state pension on basis of authorisation document </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikirja alusel makstakse riiklikku pensioni mitte rohkem kui kolm aastat j&auml;rjest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A state pension shall be paid on the basis of an authorisation document for not more than three consecutive years. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui volikirjas kehtivuse aega pole m&auml;rgitud, kehtib see &uuml;he aasta jooksul t&otilde;estamise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If no term is set out in an authorisation document, it is valid for one year as of the date of certification. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikiri peab olema t&otilde;estatud notariaalselt v&otilde;i statsionaarse raviasutuse juhi poolt, kus pension&auml;r on ravil. </eesti>
<inglise>The authorisation document shall be notarised or certified by the head of the in-patient medical institution in which the pensioner is treated. </inglise>
<eesti>(14.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.29.12.2000 - RT I 2000, 102, 673) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.12.2000 entered into force 29.12.2000 - RT I 2000, 102, 673) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui volikirja t&otilde;estab statsionaarse raviasutuse juht, kehtib see saamata j&auml;&auml;nud pensioni v&auml;ljamaksmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an authorisation document is certified by the head of an in-patient medical institution, it is valid for the payment of unreceived pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(14.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.29.12.2000 - RT I 2000, 102, 673) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.12.2000 entered into force 29.12.2000 - RT I 2000, 102, 673) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Saamata j&auml;&auml;nud pension </eesti>
<inglise>Unreceived pension </inglise>
<eesti>Kui posti kaudu makstav pension on v&auml;lja v&otilde;tmata v&auml;hemalt kuus kuud, peatatakse pensioni maksmine. </eesti>
<inglise>If a pension which is paid by post is not withdrawn for at least six months, payment of the pension shall be suspended. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rast vastava avalduse ja isikut t&otilde;endavate dokumentide seaduse (RT I 1999, 25, 365; 2000, 25, 148; 26, 150; 40, 254; 86, 550) &sect; 2 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud dokumendi esitamist makstakse pension tagantj&auml;rele v&auml;lja. </eesti>
<inglise>After submission of a corresponding claim and a document provided for in subsection 2 (2) of the Identity Documents Act (RT I 1999, 25, 365; 2000, 25, 148; 26, 150; 40, 254; 86, 550), the pension shall be paid retroactively. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni saamise erijuhud </eesti>
<inglise>Special cases of receiving state pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui kohus m&otilde;istab pension&auml;ri s&uuml;&uuml;di ja karistab teda vabadusekaotusega, peatatakse riikliku pensioni maksmine vabadusekaotuse kandmise ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a court convicts a pensioner and punishes him or her by imprisonment, payment of his or her state pension shall be suspended during imprisonment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui isiku suhtes on t&otilde;kendina kasutatud vahi alla v&otilde;tmist, peatatakse vahi all oleku ajaks riikliku pensioni maksmine. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a person is taken into custody as a preventive measure, payment of his or her state pension shall be suspended for the time the person is held in custody. </inglise>
<eesti>Pension makstakse p&auml;rast isiku &otilde;igeks m&otilde;istmist v&otilde;i kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumist tagantj&auml;rele juhul, kui kohus ei karista s&uuml;&uuml;diolevat isikut vabadusekaotusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The pension shall be paid after the person is acquitted or after a court judgment enters into force retroactively if the court does not find the person guilty and punish him or her by imprisonment. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui kohus m&auml;&auml;rab pension&auml;ri suhtes meditsiinilise iseloomuga m&otilde;jutusvahendi kohaldamise, makstakse nimetatud m&otilde;jutusvahendi kohaldamise ajal pensioni pooles rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a court orders the administration of coercive medical treatment with regard to a pensioner, his or her pension shall be paid at one half of the national pension rate during the period such treatment is administered. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1-3 nimetatud pension&auml;ril on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 13 l&otilde;ike 3 punktis 1 loetletud &uuml;lalpeetavaid, makstakse neile riiklikku pensioni j&auml;rgmises suuruses: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a pensioner specified in subsections (1) - (3) of this section has dependants listed in clause 13 (3) 1) of this Act, his or her state pension shall be paid to them in the following amounts: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;he &uuml;lalpeetava puhul 25 protsenti pensionist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in the case of one dependant, 25 per cent of the pension; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kahe &uuml;lalpeetava puhul 50 protsenti pensionist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the case of two dependants, 50 per cent of the pension; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kolme ja enama &uuml;lalpeetava puhul 75 protsenti pensionist. </eesti>
<inglise>3) in the case of three or more dependants, 75 per cent of the pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Riigieelarvest finantseeritavas hoolekandeasutuses viibivale alaealisele m&auml;&auml;ratud riiklik pension kantakse panka lapse isiklikule arvele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A state pension which is granted to a minor in a social welfare institution financed from the state budget shall be transferred to the personal bank account of the child. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Riikliku pensioni maksmisel &uuml;mardatakse 50 senti ja &uuml;le selle kroonini, summat alla 50 sendi aga ei arvestata. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Upon payment of a state pension, sums of 50 sents or more shall be rounded to the nearest kroon, but sums below 50 sents shall not be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku pensioni m&auml;&auml;ramise ja maksmise erijuhud </eesti>
<inglise>Special cases of grant and payment of state pension </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liiklus&otilde;nnetuse t&otilde;ttu isiku p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks tunnistamise v&otilde;i toitja kaotuse korral n&otilde;utakse v&auml;ljamakstud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus-, toitjakaotus- v&otilde;i rahvapension sisse liikluskindlustusega tegelevalt kindlustusandjalt, kui riiklikku pensioni saaval isikul tekib n&otilde;ude&otilde;igus liikluskindlustusega tegeleva kindlustusandja vastu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a person is declared permanently incapacitated for work due to a traffic accident or if a person loses his or her provider due to a traffic accident, the pension for incapacity for work, survivor's pension or national pension paid shall be collected from an insurer dealing in motor third party liability insurance if the right of claim against the insurer dealing in motor third party liability insurance arises for the person who receives state pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui isik ei taotlenud m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajal p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse korduvekspertiisi m&otilde;juvatel p&otilde;hjustel ning isik tunnistatakse korduvekspertiisis tagasiulatuvalt p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks, m&auml;&auml;ratakse ja makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni v&otilde;i p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse alusel rahvapensioni p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse tekkimise ajast, kuid tagasiulatuvalt mitte &uuml;le &uuml;he aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a person fails to apply for a re-examination for permanent incapacity for work during a specified term with good reason and the person is retroactively declared permanently incapacitated for work on the basis of the re-examination, a pension for incapacity for work or a national pension on the basis of permanent incapacity for work is granted and paid as of the time at which his or her permanent incapacity for work arose but for not more than one year retroactively. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) (Kehtetu - 15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(3) (Repealed - 15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Lese v&otilde;i lahutatud isiku uuesti abiellumisel s&auml;ilitatakse temale abikaasa surma v&otilde;i teadmata &auml;raolijaks tunnistamise puhul m&auml;&auml;ratud toitjakaotuspension v&otilde;i rahvapension 12 kuuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon the remarriage of a widow, widower or divorced person, a survivor's pension or national pension granted to him or her on the basis of the death of his or her spouse or the declaration of his or her spouse as missing shall be retained for twelve months. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Saamata j&auml;&auml;nud riiklik pension makstakse pension&auml;ri surma korral isikule, kellel on &otilde;igus saada toitjakaotuspensioni. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon the death of a pensioner, unreceived state pension shall be paid to persons who have the right to receive a survivor's pension. </inglise>
<eesti>Vanemal, abikaasal ja teistel perekonnaliikmetel on &otilde;igus saada saamata j&auml;&auml;nud riiklikku pensioni ka siis, kui nad ei kuulu toitjakaotuspensioniga kindlustatavate isikute hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>Parents, the spouse and other family members have the right to receive the unreceived state pension even if they are not among the persons insured by a survivor's pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(5 (1)) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi m&otilde;istes teisteks perekonnaliikmeteks on: </eesti>
<inglise>(5 (1)) Within the meaning of this section, other family members are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) laps, lapselaps, v&otilde;&otilde;raslaps; </eesti>
<inglise>1) children, grandchildren, step-children; </inglise>
<eesti>2) eestkostja, eestkostetav; </eesti>
<inglise>2) guardians, wards; </inglise>
<eesti>3) vend, &otilde;de; </eesti>
<inglise>3) brothers, sisters; </inglise>
<eesti>4) vanavanem, v&otilde;&otilde;rasvanem. </eesti>
<inglise>4) grandparents, step-parents. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Mitme perekonnaliikme samaaegsel p&ouml;&ouml;rdumisel elukohaj&auml;rgse pensioniameti poole pension&auml;ri surma t&otilde;ttu saamata j&auml;&auml;nud riikliku pensioni n&otilde;udega jagatakse saada olev pension nende vahel v&otilde;rdselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If several family members address the local pension office with a claim for unreceived state pension due to the death of a pensioner at the same time, the pension due shall be divided equally between them. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Riiklik pension makstakse p&ouml;&ouml;rdujale v&auml;lja, kui avaldus on esitatud kuue kuu jooksul pension&auml;ri surma p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A state pension shall be paid to a claimant if the claim is submitted within six months after the death of the pensioner. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) P&auml;rast pension&auml;ri surma alusetult panka tema arvele kantud v&otilde;i volikirja alusel panga v&otilde;i posti kaudu v&auml;ljamakstud riikliku pensioni summad ei kuulu p&auml;randvara koosseisu ning nimetatud summad tagastatakse panga v&otilde;i p&auml;randvara saanud isiku poolt elukohaj&auml;rgse pensioniameti vastava n&otilde;ude saamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Amounts of state pension transferred to the bank account of a pensioner or paid on the basis of an authorisation document through a bank or by post without basis after the death of the pensioner do not form part of his or her estate, and such amounts shall be returned by the bank or by the recipient of the estate upon receipt of a corresponding claim from the local pension office. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklikust pensionist kinnipidamine </eesti>
<inglise>Withholding amounts from state pension </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklikust pensionist v&otilde;ib kinni pidada: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Amounts may be withheld from a state pension: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&auml;itemenetluse seadustiku (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 1997, 43/44, 723; 1998, 41/42, 625; 51, 756; 61, 981; 103, 1695; 1999, 18, 302; 27, 380; 95, 845; 2000, 28, 167; 35, 222; 58, 376) alusel t&auml;itmisele kuuluvate lahendite alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) on the basis of a decision subject to execution pursuant to the Code of Enforcement Procedure (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 1997, 43/44, 723; 1998, 41/42, 625; 51, 756; 61, 981; 103, 1695; 1999, 18, 302; 27, 380; 95, 845; 2000, 28, 167; 35, 222; 58, 376); </inglise>
<eesti>2) elukohaj&auml;rgse pensioniameti pensionikomisjoni otsuse alusel selle pensioni sissen&otilde;udmiseks, mis on pension&auml;rile tema kuritarvituse t&otilde;ttu enam makstud. </eesti>
<inglise>2) on the basis of a decision of the pension committee of a local pension office, to collect pension which has been overpaid to a pensioner due to misconduct by him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Muid kinnipidamisi riiklikust pensionist pole lubatud teha. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Withholding amounts from a state pension in other cases is not permitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riiklikust pensionist kinnipeetav osa arvutatakse pension&auml;rile maksmiseks etten&auml;htud pensionist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The amount withheld from a state pension shall be calculated based on the pension prescribed for the pensioner. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&auml;itemenetluse seadustiku alusel t&auml;itmisele kuuluvate lahendite alusel v&otilde;idakse kinni pidada kuni 50 protsenti riiklikust pensionist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) On the basis of a decision subject to execution pursuant to the Code of Enforcement Procedure, up to 50 per cent of a state pension may be withheld. </inglise>
<eesti>Pension&auml;rile s&auml;ilitatakse v&auml;hemalt 50 protsenti rahvapensioni m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>At least 50 per cent of the national pension rate shall be retained for a pensioner. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Pensionikomisjoni otsuse alusel peetakse riiklikust pensionist kinni kuni 20 protsenti lisaks kinnipidamisele k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 4 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) On the basis of a decision of the pension committee, up to 20 per cent of a state pension shall be withheld in addition to amounts withheld pursuant to subsection (4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Pension&auml;ri kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul v&otilde;ib elukohaj&auml;rgse pensioniameti pensionikomisjoni otsuse alusel kinni pidada &uuml;le 20 protsendi pensionist. </eesti>
<inglise>Over 20 per cent of a pension may be withheld with the written consent of the pensioner on the basis of a decision of the pension committee of the local pension office. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) (Kehtetu - 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(6) (Repealed - 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui riikliku pensioni maksmine l&otilde;petatakse enne, kui pensionikomisjoni otsuse alusel kinnipeetav rohkem makstud summa on t&auml;ielikult kustutatud, n&otilde;utakse maksmata osa sisse kohtu korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If payment of a state pension terminates before an overpaid amount withheld on the basis of a decision of a pension committee is fully recovered, the unpaid amount shall be reclaimed by way of court proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Riiklikust pensionist kinnipeetava summa arvutamisel &uuml;mardatakse 50 senti ja &uuml;le selle kroonini, summat alla 50 sendi ei arvestata. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Upon calculation of the sum withheld from a pension, sums of 50 sents or more shall be rounded to the nearest kroon, but sums below 50 sents shall not be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste l&auml;bivaatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Hearing of disputes </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Elukohaj&auml;rgse pensioniameti pensionikomisjoni otsusega mitten&otilde;ustumisel v&otilde;ib pensionitaotleja (pension&auml;r) p&ouml;&ouml;rduda halduskohtusse kolme kuu jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, millal ta sai teada v&otilde;i pidi teada saama oma &otilde;iguste rikkumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a pension claimant (pensioner) does not agree with a decision of the pension committee of his or her local pension office, he or she has recourse to an administrative court within three months after the date on which he or she becomes or should have become aware of the violation of his or her rights. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arstliku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ekspertiisi otsusega mitten&otilde;ustumisel v&otilde;ib isik p&ouml;&ouml;rduda Sotsiaalkindlustusametisse, kes korraldab t&auml;iendava ekspertiisi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a person disagrees with the results of a medical examination for incapacity for work, he or she may request the Social Security Board to conduct a further examination. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iendava ekspertiisi otsusega mitten&otilde;ustumisel v&otilde;ib isik p&ouml;&ouml;rduda halduskohtusse kolme kuu jooksul otsusest teada saamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>If the person disagrees with the results of the further examination, he or she has recourse to an administrative court within three months as of the date he or she became aware of the results. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>14. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 14 </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i arvestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of accumulation period </inglise>
<eesti>Pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i arvestatakse alates 1999. aasta 1. jaanuarist. </eesti>
<inglise>Accumulation periods shall be calculated as of 1 January 1999. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;leminek t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensionilt vanaduspensionile </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer from pension for incapacity for work to old-age pension </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isikule, kellele makstakse kuni vanaduspensionieani t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni, m&auml;&auml;ratakse vanaduspensioniikka j&otilde;udmisel vanaduspension ilma pensionitaotlust n&otilde;udmata. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) When a person to whom a pension for incapacity for work is paid until attainment of the pensionable age attains such age, an old-age pension shall be granted to him or her without a pension claim. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 toodud juhul arvutatakse vanaduspension, l&auml;htudes vanaduspensioni m&auml;&auml;ramise ajaks olemasolevast pensioni&otilde;iguslikust ja pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;ist, vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 21 ja 22 s&auml;tetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case specified in subsection (1) of this section, old-age pension shall be calculated on the basis of the existing years of pensionable service and the existing accumulation period at the time of granting the old-age pension, pursuant to the provisions of &sect;&sect; 21 and 22 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui &uuml;mberarvutatud pension osutub v&auml;iksemaks varemmakstud pensionist, j&auml;tkatakse pensioni maksmist endises suuruses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a recalculated pension proves to be smaller than the pension previously paid, payment of the pension shall continue in the former amount. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;leminek invaliidsusgruppide alusel m&auml;&auml;ratud riiklikelt pensionidelt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse alusel m&auml;&auml;ratavatele riiklikele pensionidele </eesti>
<inglise>Transition from state pensions granted on basis of category of disability to state pensions granted on basis of incapacity for work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklike elatusrahade seaduse &sect;-s 9 s&auml;testatud korras m&auml;&auml;ratud invaliidsusgrupid vaadatakse &uuml;mber 3-aastase &uuml;leminekuperioodi jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Categories of disability determined pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 9 of the State Allowances Act shall be reviewed during a transitional period of three years after the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isiku suhtes, kellele on riiklike elatusrahade seaduse alusel m&auml;&auml;ratud invaliidsusgrupp t&auml;htajaliselt ja kes selleks t&auml;htajaks ei ole j&otilde;udnud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioni ikka, viiakse arstliku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ekspertiis l&auml;bi m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajal ja tema invaliidsusgrupp kehtib selle t&auml;htajani. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of persons whose category of disability has been determined for a specified term on the basis of the State Allowances Act and who within such term have not reached a pensionable age provided for in subsection 7 (1) or (2) of this Act, a medical examination for incapacity for work shall be conducted within the specified term and their categories of disability shall be valid until the expiry of such term. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Isiku suhtes, kellele on riiklike elatusrahade seaduse alusel m&auml;&auml;ratud invaliidsusgrupp t&auml;htajatult ja kes k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisel ei ole vanaduspensionieas v&otilde;i kes k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud &uuml;leminekuperioodi jooksul ei j&otilde;ua k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioniikka, viiakse arstliku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ekspertiis l&auml;bi ajavahemikul 2001. aasta 1. jaanuarist kuni 2003. aasta 31. m&auml;rtsini Pensioniameti poolt teatatud kuup&auml;eval ja tema invaliidsusgrupp kehtib kuni arstliku t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ekspertiisi l&auml;biviimiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the case of persons whose category of disability has been determined for an unspecified term on the basis of the State Allowances Act and who upon the entry into force of this Act have not reached the pensionable age or who within the transitional period provided for in subsection (1) of this section will not reach a pensionable age specified in subsections 7 (1) or (2) of this Act, a medical examination for incapacity for work shall be conducted within the period of 1 January 2001 to 31 March 2003, at a date communicated by the Pension Board, and their categories of disability shall be valid until the conduct of the medical examination for incapacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Isikul, kellele on riiklike elatusrahade seaduse alusel m&auml;&auml;ratud invaliidsusgrupp t&auml;htajatult ja kes k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisel on vanaduspensionieas v&otilde;i kes k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud &uuml;leminekuperioodi jooksul j&otilde;uab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioniikka, invaliidsusgruppi &uuml;mber ei vaadata ning see kehtib 2003. aasta 31. m&auml;rtsini. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The category of disability of a person shall not be reviewed if the category has been determined for an unspecified term on the basis of the State Allowances Act and the person has attained the pensionable age by the time of entry into force of this Act or reaches a pensionable age provided for in subsection 7 (1) or (2) of this Act within the transitional period provided for in subsection (1) of this section, and the person's category of disability shall be valid until 31 March 2003. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Isikul, kes ei ole j&otilde;udnud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioniikka, arvutatakse riiklike elatusrahade seaduse &sect; 10 kohaselt arvutatud invaliidsuspension &uuml;mber t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioniks v&otilde;i p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse alusel rahvapensioniks, arvestades k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 10 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud pensioni&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;i pensionikindlustusstaa&zcaron;i n&otilde;uet ning kohaldades j&auml;rgmisi s&auml;tteid: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the case of persons who have not attained a pensionable age provided for in subsection 7 (1) or (2) of this Act, the disability pension calculated pursuant to &sect; 10 of the State Allowances Act shall be recalculated as a pension for incapacity for work or national pension based on incapacity for work, taking into account the requirements for years of pensionable service and the accumulation period provided for in subsection 10 (2) of this Act and applying the following provisions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) I invaliidsusgrupile vastab t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotus 100 protsenti; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a loss of 100 per cent of the capacity for work corresponds to category I disability; </inglise>
<eesti>2) II invaliidsusgrupile vastab t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotus 80 protsenti; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a loss of 80 per cent of the capacity for work corresponds to category II disability; </inglise>
<eesti>3) III invaliidsusgrupile vastab t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotus 60 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a loss of 60 per cent of the capacity for work corresponds to category III disability. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) V&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatud juhtudel ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensioniikka j&otilde;udnud isikute suhtes, loetakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud &uuml;leminekuperioodi jooksul invaliidsusgrupid vastavaks p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse astmetele j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Except in the cases provided for in subsection (5) of this section and in the case of persons who have attained a pensionable age provided for in subsections 7 (1) or (2) of this Act, categories of disability are, within the transitional period provided for in subsection (1) of this section, deemed to correspond to degrees of permanent incapacity for work as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) I invaliidsusgrupile vastab t&auml;ielik t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotusega 100 protsenti; </eesti>
<inglise>1) total incapacity for work with the loss of 100 per cent of the capacity for work corresponds to category I disability; </inglise>
<eesti>2) II invaliidsusgrupile vastab osaline t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotusega 80 v&otilde;i 90 protsenti; </eesti>
<inglise>2) partial incapacity for work with the loss 80 or 90 per cent of the capacity for work corresponds to category II disability; </inglise>
<eesti>3) III invaliidsusgrupile vastab osaline t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotusega 40-70 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>3) partial incapacity for work with the loss of 40 to 70 per cent of the capacity for work corresponds to category III disability. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni ja p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse alusel rahvapensioni maksmise erijuhud </eesti>
<inglise>Special cases of payment of pension for incapacity for work and national pension based on incapacity for work </inglise>
<eesti>(15.03.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.03.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 25, 146) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) (Kehtetu - 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(1) (Repealed - 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) (Kehtetu - 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) (Repealed - 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) (Kehtetu - 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(3) (Repealed - 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Juhul kui isiku, kelle invaliidsusgruppi ei ole &uuml;mber vaadatud v&otilde;i kellele m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime kaotuse protsent on suurem endisest protsendist v&otilde;i v&otilde;rdne endise protsendiga, t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspension v&otilde;i rahvapension osutub v&auml;iksemaks varem makstud pensioni suurusest, j&auml;tkatakse pensioni maksmist endises suuruses kuni m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajani, kuid mitte kauem kui k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;igetes 1 v&otilde;i 2 s&auml;testatud vanaduspensionieani. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a pension for incapacity for work or the national pension of a person whose category of disability has not been reviewed or whose percentage of the loss of capacity for work is determined to be higher than or equal to the percentage determined previously proves to be less than the amount of the previous pension, payment of the pension shall be continued in the former amount during the specified term but nor for longer than until the person attains a pensionable age provided for in subsection 7 (1) or (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) (Kehtetu - 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </eesti>
<inglise>(5) (Repealed - 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 674) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>Varemm&auml;&auml;ratud pensionide &uuml;mberarvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Recalculation of previously granted pensions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Pension&auml;rile, kellele oli m&auml;&auml;ratud riiklik pension enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist ja kellel tekib &otilde;igus saada pensioni k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel, arvutatakse pension &uuml;mber ning kui &uuml;mberarvutatud pension osutub v&auml;iksemaks varemmakstud pensionist, j&auml;tkatakse pensioni maksmist endises suuruses kuni m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajani. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The pensions of pensioners who were granted a state pension before the entry into force of this Act and for whom the right to receive a pension arises pursuant to this Act shall be recalculated, and if the recalculated pension proves to be smaller than the previous pension, payment of the pension shall be continued in the former amount for the specified term. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pension&auml;rile, kellel ei teki &otilde;igust saada pensioni k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel, makstakse pensioni endises suuruses kuni m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajani, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 toodud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The pensions of pensioners for whom the right to receive a pension pursuant to this Act does not arise shall be paid in the former amount for the specified term, except in the case specified in subsection (4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vanaduspension&auml;rile, kellele oli m&auml;&auml;ratud riiklik pension enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist ja kellel ei teki &otilde;igust saada vanaduspensioni k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel, s&auml;ilitatakse vanaduspensioni liik ning pension arvutatakse &uuml;mber k&auml;esoleva seadusega s&auml;testatud pensionide arvutamise korra kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The class of pensions of old-age pensioners who were granted a state pension before the entry into force of this Act and for whom the right to receive an old-age pension does not arise pursuant to this Act shall be retained and the pensions shall be recalculated pursuant to the procedure provided by this Act for the calculation of pensions. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui &uuml;mberarvutatud pension osutub v&auml;iksemaks varemmakstud pensionist, j&auml;tkatakse pensioni maksmist endises suuruses kuni m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajani. </eesti>
<inglise>If the recalculated pension proves to be smaller than the previous pension, payment of the pension shall continue in the former amount for the specified term. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Pension&auml;rile, kellele makstakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 alusel abikaasa surma v&otilde;i teadmata &auml;raolijaks tunnistamise korral toitjakaotuspensioni endises suuruses, s&auml;ilitatakse tema uuesti abiellumise korral pensioni maksmine 12 kuuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon the remarriage of a pensioner, a survivor's pension paid to him or her in the former amount on the basis of the death of his or her spouse or the declaration of his or her spouse as missing and granted pursuant to subsection (2) of this section shall be retained for twelve months. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.12.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.12.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 97, 857) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50 (1). </eesti>
